{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1779192375791,"sessionID":"ses_1bfdeff9cffel20XYIHhGhKvJ3","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_00_j8iqogkP7C97etcb3p9S6467","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude-project/nestfind/design/html/frontend/A-01-landing.html"},"output":"<path>/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude-project/nestfind/design/html/frontend/A-01-landing.html</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: <!DOCTYPE html>\n2: <html lang=\"en\">\n3: <head>\n4: <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n5: <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n6: <title>NestFind — Find Your Next Home</title>\n7: <link rel=\"preconnect\" href=\"https://fonts.googleapis.com\">\n8: <link href=\"https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;500;600;700&display=swap\" rel=\"stylesheet\">\n9: <script src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@iconify/iconify@2.2.1/dist/iconify.min.js\"></script>\n10: <style>\n11: *{margin:0;padding:0;box-sizing:border-box}\n12: body{font-family:'Inter',system-ui,sans-serif;background:#0B0F1A;color:#F1F5F9;line-height:1.6}\n13: .root{max-width:1440px;margin:0 auto}\n14: .navbar{display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;padding:16px 48px;border-bottom:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08)}\n15: .nav-logo{font-size:24px;font-weight:700;background:linear-gradient(135deg,#4A90D9,#7C3AED);-webkit-background-clip:text;-webkit-text-fill-color:transparent}\n16: .nav-links{display:flex;gap:32px;align-items:center}\n17: .nav-links a{color:#94A3B8;text-decoration:none;font-size:14px;font-weight:500;transition:color 0.2s}\n18: .nav-links a:hover{color:#F1F5F9}\n19: .btn{display:inline-flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;font-weight:600;cursor:pointer;border:none;transition:all 0.2s;font-family:inherit;text-decoration:none}\n20: .btn-primary{background:linear-gradient(135deg,#4A90D9,#7C3AED);color:#fff;height:48px;padding:0 24px;border-radius:12px;font-size:14px}\n21: .btn-primary:hover{box-shadow:0 0 24px rgba(74,144,217,0.3);transform:translateY(-1px)}\n22: .btn-ghost{background:transparent;color:#F1F5F9;height:40px;padding:0 16px;border-radius:8px;font-size:14px}\n23: .btn-ghost:hover{background:rgba(255,255,255,0.06)}\n24: .hero{padding:80px 48px 64px;text-align:center}\n25: .hero h1{font-size:48px;font-weight:700;line-height:1.1;margin-bottom:16px;letter-spacing:-0.02em}\n26: .hero h1 span{background:linear-gradient(135deg,#4A90D9,#7C3AED);-webkit-background-clip:text;-webkit-text-fill-color:transparent}\n27: .hero p{color:#94A3B8;font-size:18px;max-width:560px;margin:0 auto 32px}\n28: .search-bar{display:flex;max-width:640px;margin:0 auto;gap:0}\n29: .search-bar input{flex:1;height:56px;background:rgba(255,255,255,0.04);border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08);border-right:none;border-radius:12px 0 0 12px;padding:0 20px;color:#F1F5F9;font-size:16px;font-family:inherit;outline:none}\n30: .search-bar input:focus{border-color:rgba(74,144,217,0.5);box-shadow:0 0 0 3px rgba(74,144,217,0.1)}\n31: .search-bar input::placeholder{color:#64748B}\n32: .search-bar .btn-primary{border-radius:0 12px 12px 0;height:56px;padding:0 32px;font-size:16px}\n33: .chip-row{display:flex;gap:8px;justify-content:center;margin-top:24px;flex-wrap:wrap}\n34: .chip{padding:8px 16px;background:rgba(255,255,255,0.04);border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08);border-radius:9999px;font-size:13px;color:#94A3B8;cursor:pointer;transition:all 0.2s}\n35: .chip:hover{background:rgba(255,255,255,0.08);color:#F1F5F9}\n36: .section{padding:64px 48px}\n37: .section-label{font-size:12px;font-weight:600;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.08em;color:#4A90D9;margin-bottom:8px}\n38: .section h2{font-size:36px;font-weight:700;margin-bottom:16px;letter-spacing:-0.02em}\n39: .section p.sub{color:#94A3B8;font-size:16px;max-width:560px;margin-bottom:48px}\n40: .steps{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);gap:24px}\n41: .step-card{background:rgba(255,255,255,0.04);backdrop-filter:blur(12px);border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08);border-radius:12px;padding:32px 24px;text-align:center;transition:all 0.3s}\n42: .step-card:hover{box-shadow:0 0 20px rgba(74,144,217,0.15);background:rgba(255,255,255,0.06)}\n43: .step-num{width:48px;height:48px;border-radius:12px;background:linear-gradient(135deg,#4A90D9,#7C3AED);display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;font-size:20px;font-weight:700;margin:0 auto 16px}\n44: .step-card h4{font-size:18px;font-weight:600;margin-bottom:8px}\n45: .step-card p{color:#94A3B8;font-size:14px}\n46: .property-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);gap:24px}\n47: .prop-card{background:rgba(255,255,255,0.04);backdrop-filter:blur(12px);border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08);border-radius:12px;overflow:hidden;transition:all 0.3s}\n48: .prop-card:hover{box-shadow:0 0 20px rgba(74,144,217,0.15);transform:translateY(-2px)}\n49: .prop-img{width:100%;height:200px;object-fit:cover;background:linear-gradient(135deg,rgba(74,144,217,0.3),rgba(124,58,237,0.3))}\n50: .prop-body{padding:20px}\n51: .prop-price{font-size:22px;font-weight:700}\n52: .prop-addr{color:#94A3B8;font-size:14px;margin:4px 0 8px}\n53: .prop-meta{display:flex;gap:16px;font-size:13px;color:#64748B}\n54: .badge{display:inline-block;padding:2px 10px;border-radius:9999px;font-size:11px;font-weight:600;margin-bottom:8px}\n55: .badge-new{color:#4ADE80;box-shadow:0 0 8px rgba(74,222,128,0.3)}\n56: .features{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(4,1fr);gap:24px}\n57: .feat-card{text-align:center;padding:24px}\n58: .feat-icon{width:48px;height:48px;border-radius:12px;background:rgba(74,144,217,0.1);display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;margin:0 auto 12px;color:#4A90D9}\n59: .feat-card h4{font-size:16px;font-weight:600;margin-bottom:6px}\n60: .feat-card p{color:#94A3B8;font-size:13px}\n61: footer{border-top:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08);padding:48px;display:flex;justify-content:space-between}\n62: .footer-col h5{font-size:13px;font-weight:600;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.05em;margin-bottom:16px;color:#64748B}\n63: .footer-col a{display:block;color:#94A3B8;text-decoration:none;font-size:14px;margin-bottom:8px;transition:color 0.2s}\n64: .footer-col a:hover{color:#F1F5F9}\n65: .var-nav-bar{position:fixed;top:12px;right:12px;display:flex;gap:6px;background:rgba(8,11,20,0.9);backdrop-filter:blur(16px);padding:6px 10px;border-radius:10px;z-index:9999;border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1);font-size:11px;flex-wrap:wrap;max-width:95vw}\n66: .var-nav-bar a{color:#64748B;text-decoration:none;font-size:10px;font-weight:600;padding:3px 7px;border-radius:5px;transition:all 0.2s;white-space:nowrap}\n67: .var-nav-bar a.active{background:linear-gradient(135deg,#4A90D9,#7C3AED);color:#fff}\n68: .var-nav-bar a:hover:not(.active){color:#F1F5F9;background:rgba(255,255,255,0.06)}\n69: .var-nav-bar .sep{color:rgba(255,255,255,0.15);font-size:10px}\n70: </style>\n71: </head>\n72: <body>\n73: <nav class=\"var-nav-bar\">\n74: <a href=\"A-01-landing.html\" class=\"active\">Landing</a><span class=\"sep\">|</span>\n75: <a href=\"A-02-admin-dashboard.html\">Dashboard</a><span class=\"sep\">|</span>\n76: <a href=\"A-03-detail.html\">Detail</a><span class=\"sep\">|</span>\n77: <a href=\"A-04-search.html\">Search</a><span class=\"sep\">|</span>\n78: <a href=\"A-05-login.html\">Login</a><span class=\"sep\">|</span>\n79: <a href=\"A-06-register.html\">Register</a><span class=\"sep\">|</span>\n80: <a href=\"A-07-forgot-password.html\">Reset</a><span class=\"sep\">|</span>\n81: <a href=\"A-08-favorites.html\">Favorites</a><span class=\"sep\">|</span>\n82: <a href=\"A-09-profile.html\">Profile</a><span class=\"sep\">|</span>\n83: <a href=\"A-10-admin-properties.html\">Properties</a><span class=\"sep\">|</span>\n84: <a href=\"A-11-admin-property-form.html\">PropForm</a><span class=\"sep\">|</span>\n85: <a href=\"A-12-admin-inquiries.html\">Inquiries</a><span class=\"sep\">|</span>\n86: <a href=\"A-13-admin-inquiry-detail.html\">InqDet</a><span class=\"sep\">|</span>\n87: <a href=\"A-14-admin-users.html\">Users</a><span class=\"sep\">|</span>\n88: <a href=\"A-15-admin-user-detail.html\">UsrDet</a>\n89: </nav>\n90: <div class=\"root\">\n91: <nav class=\"navbar\">\n92: <div class=\"nav-logo\">NestFind</div>\n93: <div class=\"nav-links\">\n94: <a href=\"A-04-search.html\">Browse</a>\n95: <a href=\"#\">How It Works</a>\n96: <a href=\"#\">For Owners</a>\n97: <a href=\"A-05-login.html\" class=\"btn btn-ghost\">Sign In</a>\n98: <a href=\"A-06-register.html\" class=\"btn btn-primary\">Join Now</a>\n99: </div>\n100: </nav>\n101: <section class=\"hero\">\n102: <h1>Find Your <span>Perfect Nest</span>,<br>Without the Noise</h1>\n103: <p>Browse thousands of verified rental properties. Clean, ad-free, and focused on what matters — finding your next home.</p>\n104: <div class=\"search-bar\">\n105: <input type=\"text\" placeholder=\"Enter city, neighborhood, or ZIP code...\">\n106: <button class=\"btn btn-primary\">Search Properties</button>\n107: </div>\n108: <div class=\"chip-row\">\n109: <span class=\"chip\">Apartments</span>\n110: <span class=\"chip\">Houses</span>\n111: <span class=\"chip\">Condos</span>\n112: <span class=\"chip\">Pet-Friendly</span>\n113: <span class=\"chip\">Under $2,000</span>\n114: </div>\n115: </section>\n116: <section class=\"section\">\n117: <div class=\"section-label\">How It Works</div>\n118: <h2>Three steps to your next home</h2>\n119: <p class=\"sub\">NestFind makes rental hunting simple. No ads, no clutter, just homes you'll love.</p>\n120: <div class=\"steps\">\n121: <div class=\"step-card\">\n122: <div class=\"step-num\">1</div>\n123: <h4>Search & Filter</h4>\n124: <p>Enter your preferred location and refine by price, beds, and property type. Results update instantly.</p>\n125: </div>\n126: <div class=\"step-card\">\n127: <div class=\"step-num\">2</div>\n128: <h4>Explore & Save</h4>\n129: <p>Browse photos, check amenities, and view locations on the map. Save favorites with one click.</p>\n130: </div>\n131: <div class=\"step-card\">\n132: <div class=\"step-num\">3</div>\n133: <h4>Inquire & Move</h4>\n134: <p>Send an inquiry directly to the property manager. Simple form, no lengthy applications.</p>\n135: </div>\n136: </div>\n137: </section>\n138: <section class=\"section\">\n139: <div class=\"section-label\">Featured Properties</div>\n140: <h2>Homes you might love</h2>\n141: <p class=\"sub\">Hand-picked listings from our curated collection.</p>\n142: <div class=\"property-grid\">\n143: <div class=\"prop-card\">\n144: <div class=\"prop-img\" style=\"background:linear-gradient(135deg,#1e3a5f,#2d1b69);display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;font-size:48px;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.1)\">🏠</div>\n145: <div class=\"prop-body\">\n146: <span class=\"badge badge-new\">Available Now</span>\n147: <div class=\"prop-price\">$1,850<span style=\"font-size:14px;font-weight:400;color:#94A3B8\">/mo</span></div>\n148: <div class=\"prop-addr\">1420 Pine Street, San Francisco, CA</div>\n149: <div class=\"prop-meta\"><span>2 bd</span><span>1 ba</span><span>850 sqft</span><span>Apartment</span></div>\n150: </div>\n151: </div>\n152: <div class=\"prop-card\">\n153: <div class=\"prop-img\" style=\"background:linear-gradient(135deg,#3d266b,#1a3a5c);display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;font-size:48px;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.1)\">🏡</div>\n154: <div class=\"prop-body\">\n155: <span class=\"badge badge-new\">Available Now</span>\n156: <div class=\"prop-price\">$2,950<span style=\"font-size:14px;font-weight:400;color:#94A3B8\">/mo</span></div>\n157: <div class=\"prop-addr\">381 Oak Avenue, Austin, TX</div>\n158: <div class=\"prop-meta\"><span>3 bd</span><span>2 ba</span><span>1,200 sqft</span><span>House</span></div>\n159: </div>\n160: </div>\n161: <div class=\"prop-card\">\n162: <div class=\"prop-img\" style=\"background:linear-gradient(135deg,#1a3a5c,#3d266b);display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;font-size:48px;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.1)\">🏢</div>\n163: <div class=\"prop-body\">\n164: <span class=\"badge badge-new\">Available Now</span>\n165: <div class=\"prop-price\">$2,200<span style=\"font-size:14px;font-weight:400;color:#94A3B8\">/mo</span></div>\n166: <div class=\"prop-addr\">750 Market Street, Portland, OR</div>\n167: <div class=\"prop-meta\"><span>1 bd</span><span>1 ba</span><span>720 sqft</span><span>Condo</span></div>\n168: </div>\n169: </div>\n170: </div>\n171: </section>\n172: <section class=\"section\">\n173: <div class=\"section-label\">Why NestFind</div>\n174: <h2>Built for renters, not advertisers</h2>\n175: <p class=\"sub\">We focused on what actually matters when finding a rental.</p>\n176: <div class=\"features\">\n177: <div class=\"feat-card\"><div class=\"feat-icon\"><iconify-icon icon=\"mdi:eye-off-outline\" width=\"24\"></iconify-icon></div><h4>Ad-Free Browsing</h4><p>No sponsored listings cluttering your search. Every result is organic.</p></div>\n178: <div class=\"feat-card\"><div class=\"feat-icon\"><iconify-icon icon=\"mdi:lightning-bolt\" width=\"24\"></iconify-icon></div><h4>Instant Filters</h4><p>Real-time filtering by price, beds, and type. No page reloads.</p></div>\n179: <div class=\"feat-card\"><div class=\"feat-icon\"><iconify-icon icon=\"mdi:heart-outline\" width=\"24\"></iconify-icon></div><h4>Quick Favorites</h4><p>Save properties with one click. Access your favorites from anywhere.</p></div>\n180: <div class=\"feat-card\"><div class=\"feat-icon\"><iconify-icon icon=\"mdi:map-marker-outline\" width=\"24\"></iconify-icon></div><h4>Map View</h4><p>See exactly where each property is. Integrated Google Maps on every listing.</p></div>\n181: </div>\n182: </section>\n183: <footer>\n184: <div class=\"footer-col\"><h5>NestFind</h5><a href=\"#\">About</a><a href=\"#\">Careers</a><a href=\"#\">Press</a><a href=\"#\">Blog</a></div>\n185: <div class=\"footer-col\"><h5>Renters</h5><a href=\"A-04-search.html\">Browse Properties</a><a href=\"#\">How It Works</a><a href=\"#\">Renter Guide</a><a href=\"#\">Safety Tips</a></div>\n186: <div class=\"footer-col\"><h5>Owners</h5><a href=\"#\">List a Property</a><a href=\"#\">Owner Dashboard</a><a href=\"#\">Pricing</a><a href=\"#\">Resources</a></div>\n187: <div class=\"footer-col\"><h5>Support</h5><a href=\"#\">Help Center</a><a href=\"#\">Contact Us</a><a href=\"#\">Privacy Policy</a><a href=\"#\">Terms of Service</a></div>\n188: </footer>\n189: </div>\n190: </body>\n191: </html>\n\n(End of file - total 191 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n<meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n<title>NestFind — Find Your Next Home</title>\n<link rel=\"preconnect\" href=\"https://fonts.googleapis.com\">\n<link href=\"https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;500;600;700&display=swap\" rel=\"stylesheet\">\n<script src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@iconify/iconify@2.2.1/dist/iconify.min.js\"></script>\n<style>\n*{margin:0;padding:0;box-sizing:border-box}\nbody{font-family:'Inter',system-ui,sans-serif;background:#0B0F1A;color:#F1F5F9;line-height:1.6}\n.root{max-width:1440px;margin:0 auto}\n.navbar{display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;padding:16px 48px;border-bottom:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08)}\n.nav-logo{font-size:24px;font-weight:700;background:linear-gradient(135deg,#4A90D9,#7C3AED);-webkit-background-clip:text;-webkit-text-fill-color:transparent}\n.nav-links{display:flex;gap:32px;align-items:center}\n.nav-links a{color:#94A3B8;text-decoration:none;font-size:14px;font-weight:500;transition:color 0.2s}\n.nav-links a:hover{color:#F1F5F9}\n.btn{display:inline-flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;font-weight:600;cursor:pointer;border:none;transition:all 0.2s;font-family:inherit;text-decoration:none}\n.btn-primary{background:linear-gradient(135deg,#4A90D9,#7C3AED);color:#fff;height:48px;padding:0 24px;border-radius:12px;font-size:14px}","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".claude-project/nestfind/design/html/frontend/A-01-landing.html","time":{"start":1779192375498,"end":1779192375789}},"id":"prt_e40212256001p2PcX86V2g6Kae","sessionID":"ses_1bfdeff9cffel20XYIHhGhKvJ3","messageID":"msg_e4021040c0013iNRwEANypdde1"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1779192377553,"sessionID":"ses_1bfdeff9cffel20XYIHhGhKvJ3","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_01_peqWrkWz47sACDJ0q4783657","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude/react/docs/component-patterns.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude/react/docs/component-patterns.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Component Patterns\n2: \n3: Modern component architecture using Shadcn/UI, Tailwind CSS, and TypeScript.\n4: \n5: ---\n6: \n7: ## Function Component Pattern (PREFERRED)\n8: \n9: ### Why Function Components\n10: \n11: All components use function components with TypeScript for:\n12: \n13: - Explicit type safety for props\n14: - Consistent component signatures\n15: - Clear prop interface documentation\n16: - Better IDE autocomplete\n17: \n18: ### Basic Pattern\n19: \n20: ```typescript\n21: import { Button } from '~/components/ui/button';\n22: import { cn } from '~/lib/utils';\n23: \n24: interface MyComponentProps {\n25:   /** User ID to display */\n26:   userId: number;\n27:   /** Optional callback when action occurs */\n28:   onAction?: () => void;\n29: }\n30: \n31: export default function MyComponent({ userId, onAction }: MyComponentProps) {\n32:   return (\n33:     <div className=\"p-4\">\n34:       User: {userId}\n35:       <Button onClick={onAction}>Action</Button>\n36:     </div>\n37:   );\n38: }\n39: ```\n40: \n41: **Key Points:**\n42: \n43: - Props interface defined separately with JSDoc comments\n44: - Destructure props in parameters\n45: - Default export at bottom\n46: - Use Tailwind classes for styling\n47: \n48: ---\n49: \n50: ## Shadcn/UI Component Usage\n51: \n52: ### Available Components\n53: \n54: Shadcn/UI components are in `~/components/ui/`:\n55: \n56: ```typescript\n57: // Buttons\n58: import { Button, buttonVariants } from '~/components/ui/button';\n59: \n60: // Forms\n61: import { Input } from '~/components/ui/input';\n62: import { Label } from '~/components/ui/label';\n63: import {\n64:   Form,\n65:   FormControl,\n66:   FormField,\n67:   FormItem,\n68:   FormLabel,\n69:   FormMessage,\n70: } from '~/components/ui/form';\n71: \n72: // Cards\n73: import { Card, CardContent, CardHeader, CardTitle } from '~/components/ui/card';\n74: ```\n75: \n76: ### Button Component\n77: \n78: ```typescript\n79: import { Button } from '~/components/ui/button';\n80: \n81: // Variants\n82: <Button variant=\"default\">Primary</Button>\n83: <Button variant=\"secondary\">Secondary</Button>\n84: <Button variant=\"destructive\">Delete</Button>\n85: <Button variant=\"outline\">Outlined</Button>\n86: <Button variant=\"ghost\">Ghost</Button>\n87: <Button variant=\"link\">Link</Button>\n88: \n89: // Sizes\n90: <Button size=\"sm\">Small</Button>\n91: <Button size=\"default\">Default</Button>\n92: <Button size=\"lg\">Large</Button>\n93: <Button size=\"icon\"><Icon /></Button>\n94: \n95: // States\n96: <Button disabled>Disabled</Button>\n97: <Button className=\"w-full\">Full Width</Button>\n98: ```\n99: \n100: ### Card Component\n101: \n102: ```typescript\n103: import { Card, CardContent, CardHeader, CardTitle } from '~/components/ui/card';\n104: \n105: <Card className=\"w-full max-w-md\">\n106:   <CardHeader>\n107:     <CardTitle>Card Title</CardTitle>\n108:   </CardHeader>\n109:   <CardContent className=\"space-y-4\">\n110:     <p>Card content goes here</p>\n111:   </CardContent>\n112: </Card>\n113: ```\n114: \n115: ### Form Components (MANDATORY PATTERN — all forms must use this)\n116: \n117: ```typescript\n118: import { useForm } from 'react-hook-form';\n119: import { zodResolver } from '@hookform/resolvers/zod';\n120: import { z } from 'zod';\n121: import { Button } from '~/components/ui/button';\n122: import { Input } from '~/components/ui/input';\n123: import {\n124:   Form,\n125:   FormControl,\n126:   FormField,\n127:   FormItem,\n128:   FormLabel,\n129:   FormMessage,\n130: } from '~/components/ui/form';\n131: \n132: const schema = z.object({\n133:   email: z.string().email(),\n134:   password: z.string().min(6),\n135: });\n136: \n137: type FormData = z.infer<typeof schema>;\n138: \n139: export default function LoginForm() {\n140:   const form = useForm<FormData>({\n141:     resolver: zodResolver(schema),\n142:     defaultValues: { email: '', password: '' },\n143:   });\n144: \n145:   return (\n146:     <Form {...form}>\n147:       <form onSubmit={form.handleSubmit(onSubmit)} className=\"space-y-4\">\n148:         <FormField\n149:           control={form.control}\n150:           name=\"email\"\n151:           render={({ field }) => (\n152:             <FormItem>\n153:               <FormLabel>Email</FormLabel>\n154:               <FormControl>\n155:                 <Input placeholder=\"Enter email\" {...field} />\n156:               </FormControl>\n157:               <FormMessage />\n158:             </FormItem>\n159:           )}\n160:         />\n161:         <Button type=\"submit\">Submit</Button>\n162:       </form>\n163:     </Form>\n164:   );\n165: }\n166: ```\n167: \n168: ---\n169: \n170: ## CVA (Class Variance Authority)\n171: \n172: ### What is CVA\n173: \n174: CVA is used for component variants in Shadcn/UI. It creates type-safe variant props.\n175: \n176: ### Example from Button Component\n177: \n178: ```typescript\n179: import { cva, type VariantProps } from 'class-variance-authority';\n180: import { cn } from '~/lib/utils';\n181: \n182: const buttonVariants = cva(\n183:   // Base styles applied to all buttons\n184:   'inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-md text-sm font-medium transition-all',\n185:   {\n186:     variants: {\n187:       variant: {\n188:         default: 'bg-primary text-primary-foreground hover:bg-primary/90',\n189:         destructive: 'bg-destructive text-white hover:bg-destructive/90',\n190:         outline: 'border bg-background hover:bg-accent',\n191:         secondary: 'bg-secondary text-secondary-foreground hover:bg-secondary/80',\n192:         ghost: 'hover:bg-accent hover:text-accent-foreground',\n193:         link: 'text-primary underline-offset-4 hover:underline',\n194:       },\n195:       size: {\n196:         default: 'h-9 px-4 py-2',\n197:         sm: 'h-8 px-3',\n198:         lg: 'h-10 px-6',\n199:         icon: 'size-9',\n200:       },\n201:     },\n202:     defaultVariants: {\n203:       variant: 'default',\n204:       size: 'default',\n205:     },\n206:   }\n207: );\n208: \n209: // Usage in component\n210: function Button({\n211:   className,\n212:   variant,\n213:   size,\n214:   ...props\n215: }: React.ComponentProps<'button'> & VariantProps<typeof buttonVariants>) {\n216:   return (\n217:     <button\n218:       className={cn(buttonVariants({ variant, size, className }))}\n219:       {...props}\n220:     />\n221:   );\n222: }\n223: ```\n224: \n225: ---\n226: \n227: ## When to Add a Variant vs Use className (MANDATORY)\n228: \n229: All reusable components must follow these rules:\n230: \n231: 1. **Every reusable component MUST accept a `className` prop** — this allows call-site-specific layout overrides\n232: 2. **Add a cva variant when:**\n233:    - The style combination appears at 2+ call sites\n234:    - It represents a semantic state (error, success, warning, loading, ghost, compact)\n235:    - It changes the visual identity of the component (not just layout)\n236: 3. **Use `className` when:**\n237:    - The override is context-specific and used at only 1 call site\n238:    - It's a layout concern (width, height, padding offset, positioning)\n239:    - It's a dynamic value passed from props (e.g., `className={style.text}`)\n240: \n241: ```typescript\n242: // ✅ CORRECT — Semantic state as variant\n243: <Input variant=\"error\" />\n244: \n245: // ✅ CORRECT — One-off layout as className\n246: <Input className=\"pl-10\" />\n247: \n248: // ❌ WRONG — Duplicated error classes at call sites\n249: <Input className=\"border-red-400 focus:ring-2 focus:ring-red-500/20\" />\n250: \n251: // ❌ WRONG — Creating a new component for a style difference\n252: // Instead, add a variant to the existing component\n253: ```\n254: \n255: ---\n256: \n257: ## cn() Utility for Class Merging\n258: \n259: ### What is cn()\n260: \n261: `cn()` combines `clsx` and `tailwind-merge` for conditional class merging:\n262: \n263: ```typescript\n264: // ~/lib/utils.ts\n265: import { clsx, type ClassValue } from 'clsx';\n266: import { twMerge } from 'tailwind-merge';\n267: \n268: export function cn(...inputs: ClassValue[]) {\n269:   return twMerge(clsx(inputs));\n270: }\n271: ```\n272: \n273: ### Usage Examples\n274: \n275: ```typescript\n276: import { cn } from '~/lib/utils';\n277: \n278: // Conditional classes\n279: <div className={cn(\n280:   'p-4 bg-background',\n281:   isActive && 'bg-primary text-primary-foreground',\n282:   isDisabled && 'opacity-50 pointer-events-none'\n283: )} />\n284: \n285: // Merging with overrides\n286: <Button className={cn(\n287:   buttonVariants({ variant: 'default' }),\n288:   'w-full' // Override width\n289: )} />\n290: \n291: // Array of conditions\n292: <div className={cn([\n293:   'base-class',\n294:   condition1 && 'class-1',\n295:   condition2 && 'class-2',\n296: ])} />\n297: ```\n298: \n299: ---\n300: \n301: ## asChild Pattern (Radix UI)\n302: \n303: ### What is asChild\n304: \n305: The `asChild` prop allows composing components with custom elements:\n306: \n307: ```typescript\n308: import { Button } from '~/components/ui/button';\n309: import { Link } from 'react-router';\n310: \n311: // Button as Link\n312: <Button asChild>\n313:   <Link to=\"/dashboard\">Go to Dashboard</Link>\n314: </Button>\n315: \n316: // Button as anchor\n317: <Button asChild variant=\"link\">\n318:   <a href=\"https://example.com\">External Link</a>\n319: </Button>\n320: ```\n321: \n322: ### How it Works\n323: \n324: The Button uses Radix's `Slot` component:\n325: \n326: ```typescript\n327: import { Slot } from '@radix-ui/react-slot';\n328: \n329: function Button({ asChild = false, ...props }) {\n330:   const Comp = asChild ? Slot : 'button';\n331:   return <Comp {...props} />;\n332: }\n333: ```\n334: \n335: ### IMPORTANT: asChild + Link Anti-Pattern\n336: \n337: **NEVER use `asChild` with `Link` inside `DropdownMenuItem`:**\n338: \n339: ```typescript\n340: // ❌ CAUSES VISUAL \"BLINK\" ON FIRST RENDER\n341: <DropdownMenuItem asChild>\n342:   <Link to={`/dashboard/users/${user.id}`}>\n343:     <Eye className=\"mr-2 h-4 w-4\" />\n344:     View Details\n345:   </Link>\n346: </DropdownMenuItem>\n347: \n348: // ✅ USE onClick with navigate() INSTEAD\n349: <DropdownMenuItem onClick={() => navigate(`/dashboard/users/${user.id}`)}>\n350:   <Eye className=\"mr-2 h-4 w-4\" />\n351:   View Details\n352: </DropdownMenuItem>\n353: ```\n354: \n355: **Better: Use the ActionMenu Component**\n356: \n357: For table action menus, use the reusable `ActionMenu` component:\n358: \n359: ```typescript\n360: import { ActionMenu } from '~/components/ui/action-menu';\n361: \n362: <ActionMenu\n363:   items={[\n364:     {\n365:       label: 'View Details',\n366:       icon: <Eye className=\"mr-2 h-4 w-4\" />,\n367:       href: `/dashboard/users/${user.id}`,  // Uses navigate() internally\n368:     },\n369:     {\n370:       label: 'Delete',\n371:       icon: <Trash2 className=\"mr-2 h-4 w-4\" />,\n372:       onClick: () => handleDelete(user.id),\n373:       variant: 'destructive',\n374:     },\n375:   ]}\n376: />\n377: ```\n378: \n379: ---\n380: \n381: ## Component Structure Template\n382: \n383: ### Recommended Order\n384: \n385: ```typescript\n386: import { useState, useCallback, useMemo, useEffect } from 'react';\n387: import { Link } from 'react-router';\n388: \n389: // Redux\n390: import { useAppDispatch, useAppSelector } from '~/redux/store/hooks';\n391: \n392: // UI Components\n393: import { Button } from '~/components/ui/button';\n394: import { Card, CardContent, CardHeader } from '~/components/ui/card';\n395: \n396: // Utilities\n397: import { cn } from '~/lib/utils';\n398: \n399: // Types\n400: import type { User } from '~/types/user';\n401: \n402: // 1. PROPS INTERFACE (with JSDoc)\n403: interface MyComponentProps {\n404:   /** The ID of the entity to display */\n405:   entityId: number;\n406:   /** Optional callback when action completes */\n407:   onComplete?: () => void;\n408:   /** Display mode */\n409:   mode?: 'view' | 'edit';\n410: }\n411: \n412: // 2. COMPONENT DEFINITION\n413: export default function MyComponent({\n414:   entityId,\n415:   onComplete,\n416:   mode = 'view',\n417: }: MyComponentProps) {\n418:   // 3. HOOKS (in this order)\n419:   // - Redux hooks\n420:   const dispatch = useAppDispatch();\n421:   const user = useAppSelector((state) => state.user.currentUser);\n422:   const loading = useAppSelector((state) => state.user.loading);\n423: \n424:   // - Local state\n425:   const [selectedItem, setSelectedItem] = useState<string | null>(null);\n426:   const [isEditing, setIsEditing] = useState(mode === 'edit');\n427: \n428:   // - Memoized values\n429:   const filteredData = useMemo(() => {\n430:     return data.filter((item) => item.active);\n431:   }, [data]);\n432: \n433:   // - Effects\n434:   useEffect(() => {\n435:     // Setup\n436:     return () => {\n437:       // Cleanup\n438:     };\n439:   }, []);\n440: \n441:   // 4. EVENT HANDLERS (with useCallback for passed handlers)\n442:   const handleItemSelect = useCallback((itemId: string) => {\n443:     setSelectedItem(itemId);\n444:   }, []);\n445: \n446:   const handleSave = useCallback(async () => {\n447:     try {\n448:       // Save logic\n449:       onComplete?.();\n450:     } catch (error) {\n451:       console.error('Failed to save:', error);\n452:     }\n453:   }, [onComplete]);\n454: \n455:   // 5. RENDER\n456:   return (\n457:     <Card className=\"w-full max-w-md\">\n458:       <CardHeader>\n459:         <h2 className=\"text-xl font-bold\">My Component</h2>\n460:       </CardHeader>\n461:       <CardContent className=\"space-y-4\">\n462:         <p className={cn('text-muted-foreground', loading && 'opacity-50')}>\n463:           {user?.email}\n464:         </p>\n465:         <Button onClick={handleSave} disabled={loading}>\n466:           {loading ? 'Loading...' : 'Save'}\n467:         </Button>\n468:       </CardContent>\n469:     </Card>\n470:   );\n471: }\n472: ```\n473: \n474: ---\n475: \n476: ## Component Separation\n477: \n478: ### When to Split Components\n479: \n480: **Split into multiple components when:**\n481: \n482: - Component exceeds 200 lines\n483: - Multiple distinct responsibilities\n484: - Reusable sections\n485: - Complex nested JSX\n486: \n487: **Example:**\n488: \n489: ```typescript\n490: // ❌ AVOID - Monolithic\n491: function MassivePage() {\n492:   // 500+ lines\n493:   // Header logic\n494:   // Form logic\n495:   // Table logic\n496:   // Modal logic\n497: }\n498: \n499: // ✅ PREFERRED - Modular\n500: function Page() {\n501:   return (\n502:     <div className=\"space-y-6\">\n503:       <PageHeader />\n504:       <SearchForm onSearch={handleSearch} />\n505:       <DataTable data={filteredData} />\n506:       <ActionModal open={isOpen} onClose={handleClose} />\n507:     </div>\n508:   );\n509: }\n510: ```\n511: \n512: ### When to Keep Together\n513: \n514: **Keep in same file when:**\n515: \n516: - Component < 100 lines\n517: - Tightly coupled logic\n518: - Not reusable elsewhere\n519: - Simple presentation component\n520: \n521: ---\n522: \n523: ## Lazy Loading Pattern\n524: \n525: ### When to Lazy Load\n526: \n527: Lazy load components that are:\n528: \n529: - Heavy (DataGrid, charts, rich text editors)\n530: - Route-level components\n531: - Modal/dialog content (not shown initially)\n532: - Below-the-fold content\n533: \n534: ### How to Lazy Load\n535: \n536: ```typescript\n537: import { lazy, Suspense } from 'react';\n538: \n539: // Lazy load heavy component\n540: const HeavyEditor = lazy(() => import('./HeavyEditor'));\n541: \n542: // Usage with Suspense\n543: function Page() {\n544:   return (\n545:     <Suspense fallback={<div>Loading...</div>}>\n546:       <HeavyEditor />\n547:     </Suspense>\n548:   );\n549: }\n550: ```\n551: \n552: ---\n553: \n554: ## Component Communication\n555: \n556: ### Props Down, Events Up\n557: \n558: ```typescript\n559: // Parent\n560: function Parent() {\n561:   const [selectedId, setSelectedId] = useState<string | null>(null);\n562: \n563:   return (\n564:     <Child\n565:       data={data} // Props down\n566:       onSelect={setSelectedId} // Events up\n567:     />\n568:   );\n569: }\n570: \n571: // Child\n572: interface ChildProps {\n573:   data: Data[];\n574:   onSelect: (id: string) => void;\n575: }\n576: \n577: export default function Child({ data, onSelect }: ChildProps) {\n578:   return (\n579:     <ul>\n580:       {data.map((item) => (\n581:         <li key={item.id} onClick={() => onSelect(item.id)}>\n582:           {item.name}\n583:         </li>\n584:       ))}\n585:     </ul>\n586:   );\n587: }\n588: ```\n589: \n590: ### Using Redux for Shared State\n591: \n592: ```typescript\n593: // When state needs to be shared across components\n594: import { useAppDispatch, useAppSelector } from '~/redux/store/hooks';\n595: import { selectItem } from '~/redux/features/itemSlice';\n596: \n597: function Child() {\n598:   const dispatch = useAppDispatch();\n599:   const selectedId = useAppSelector((state) => state.item.selectedId);\n600: \n601:   const handleSelect = (id: string) => {\n602:     dispatch(selectItem(id));\n603:   };\n604: \n605:   return <div onClick={() => handleSelect('123')}>Select</div>;\n606: }\n607: ```\n608: \n609: ---\n610: \n611: ## Summary\n612: \n613: **Modern Component Recipe:**\n614: \n615: 1. Function components with TypeScript props interface\n616: 2. Shadcn/UI components from `~/components/ui/`\n617: 3. `cn()` utility for conditional classes\n618: 4. Tailwind CSS for styling\n619: 5. `useAppSelector` and `useAppDispatch` for Redux\n620: 6. Event handlers with `useCallback` when passed to children\n621: 7. Default export at bottom\n622: \n623: ---\n624: \n625: ## MANDATORY: Async State Handling\n626: \n627: Every component that fetches data MUST handle all three states:\n628: \n629: ```typescript\n630: // MANDATORY: Loading state\n631: if (isLoading) return <LoadingSkeleton />;\n632: \n633: // MANDATORY: Error state\n634: if (error) return <ErrorState message={error.message} onRetry={refetch} />;\n635: \n636: // MANDATORY: Empty state (distinct from error)\n637: if (!data?.length) return <EmptyState title=\"No items found\" />;\n638: \n639: // Happy path\n640: return <DataList items={data} />;\n641: ```\n642: \n643: **Rules:**\n644: - Loading skeleton (not spinner) for initial data loads\n645: - Error state with retry button for API failures\n646: - Empty state for zero results (NOT the same component as error)\n647: - Error boundaries wrapping route-level components for uncaught errors\n648: \n649: ## MANDATORY: No Business Logic in Components\n650: \n651: Components must only handle rendering and event delegation:\n652: \n653: ```typescript\n654: // BAD: Business logic in component\n655: const filteredUsers = users.filter(u => u.role === 'admin' && u.isActive);\n656: const sortedUsers = filteredUsers.sort((a, b) => a.name.localeCompare(b.name));\n657: \n658: // GOOD: Logic in selector/utility\n659: const activeAdmins = useAppSelector(selectActiveAdmins);\n660: ```\n661: \n662: **See Also:**\n663: \n664: - [styling-guide.md](styling-guide.md) - Tailwind CSS patterns\n665: - [common-patterns.md](common-patterns.md) - Form patterns\n666: - [complete-examples.md](complete-examples.md) - Full working examples\n\n(End of file - total 666 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Component Patterns\n\nModern component architecture using Shadcn/UI, Tailwind CSS, and TypeScript.\n\n---\n\n## Function Component Pattern (PREFERRED)\n\n### Why Function Components\n\nAll components use function components with TypeScript for:\n\n- Explicit type safety for props\n- Consistent component signatures\n- Clear prop interface documentation\n- Better IDE autocomplete\n\n### Basic Pattern\n\n```typescript","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".claude/react/docs/component-patterns.md","time":{"start":1779192377268,"end":1779192377552}},"id":"prt_e40212af60011xKYUXSDdCHQU6","sessionID":"ses_1bfdeff9cffel20XYIHhGhKvJ3","messageID":"msg_e4021040c0013iNRwEANypdde1"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1779192379257,"sessionID":"ses_1bfdeff9cffel20XYIHhGhKvJ3","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_02_uFIe5BCY0LvIBQCQb0hJ5265","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude/react/docs/styling-guide.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude/react/docs/styling-guide.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Styling Guide\n2: \n3: Modern styling patterns using Tailwind CSS 4, Shadcn/UI, and CSS variables.\n4: \n5: ---\n6: \n7: ## Core Concepts\n8: \n9: ### Tailwind CSS 4\n10: \n11: The project uses Tailwind CSS 4 with utility-first styling:\n12: \n13: ```typescript\n14: // Direct utility classes\n15: <div className=\"p-4 mb-3 flex flex-col gap-2\">\n16:   Content\n17: </div>\n18: ```\n19: \n20: ### cn() Utility\n21: \n22: Use `cn()` for conditional class merging (combines `clsx` + `tailwind-merge`):\n23: \n24: ```typescript\n25: import { cn } from '~/lib/utils';\n26: \n27: <div className={cn(\n28:   'p-4 bg-background',\n29:   isActive && 'bg-primary text-primary-foreground',\n30:   isDisabled && 'opacity-50 pointer-events-none'\n31: )} />\n32: ```\n33: \n34: ---\n35: \n36: ## CSS Variables (Theme)\n37: \n38: ### Available Color Variables\n39: \n40: Colors are defined in `~/styles/app.css` using oklch color space:\n41: \n42: ```css\n43: :root {\n44:   --background: oklch(1 0 0);\n45:   --foreground: oklch(0.145 0 0);\n46:   --primary: oklch(0.205 0 0);\n47:   --primary-foreground: oklch(0.985 0 0);\n48:   --secondary: oklch(0.97 0 0);\n49:   --secondary-foreground: oklch(0.205 0 0);\n50:   --muted: oklch(0.97 0 0);\n51:   --muted-foreground: oklch(0.556 0 0);\n52:   --accent: oklch(0.97 0 0);\n53:   --accent-foreground: oklch(0.205 0 0);\n54:   --destructive: oklch(0.577 0.245 27.325);\n55:   --border: oklch(0.922 0 0);\n56:   --input: oklch(0.922 0 0);\n57:   --ring: oklch(0.708 0 0);\n58:   /* Chart colors, sidebar colors, etc. */\n59: }\n60: ```\n61: \n62: ### Using Color Variables\n63: \n64: ```typescript\n65: // Via Tailwind classes (preferred)\n66: <div className=\"bg-background text-foreground\" />\n67: <div className=\"bg-primary text-primary-foreground\" />\n68: <div className=\"text-muted-foreground\" />\n69: <div className=\"border-border\" />\n70: <div className=\"bg-destructive\" />\n71: \n72: // Semantic usage\n73: <p className=\"text-muted-foreground\">Secondary text</p>\n74: <button className=\"bg-primary text-primary-foreground\">Button</button>\n75: <div className=\"border border-input\">Input border</div>\n76: ```\n77: \n78: ---\n79: \n80: ## Dark Mode\n81: \n82: ### How Dark Mode Works\n83: \n84: Dark mode is activated by adding `.dark` class to the document:\n85: \n86: ```css\n87: .dark {\n88:   --background: oklch(0.145 0 0);\n89:   --foreground: oklch(0.985 0 0);\n90:   --primary: oklch(0.922 0 0);\n91:   --primary-foreground: oklch(0.205 0 0);\n92:   /* ... other overrides */\n93: }\n94: ```\n95: \n96: ### Dark Mode Variants\n97: \n98: ```typescript\n99: // Automatic with semantic colors (preferred)\n100: <div className=\"bg-background text-foreground\" />\n101: // Light: white bg, dark text\n102: // Dark: dark bg, light text\n103: \n104: // Explicit dark mode variants\n105: <div className=\"bg-white dark:bg-gray-900\" />\n106: <div className=\"text-gray-900 dark:text-white\" />\n107: ```\n108: \n109: ---\n110: \n111: ## Common Utility Classes\n112: \n113: ### Spacing\n114: \n115: ```typescript\n116: // Padding\n117: <div className=\"p-4\" />      // All sides: 1rem (16px)\n118: <div className=\"px-4\" />     // Horizontal: 1rem\n119: <div className=\"py-4\" />     // Vertical: 1rem\n120: <div className=\"pt-4\" />     // Top only: 1rem\n121: <div className=\"p-2\" />      // All sides: 0.5rem (8px)\n122: \n123: // Margin\n124: <div className=\"m-4\" />      // All sides\n125: <div className=\"mx-auto\" />  // Center horizontally\n126: <div className=\"mt-4 mb-2\" />\n127: \n128: // Gap (for flex/grid)\n129: <div className=\"gap-4\" />    // 1rem gap\n130: <div className=\"gap-2\" />    // 0.5rem gap\n131: ```\n132: \n133: ### Flexbox\n134: \n135: ```typescript\n136: // Basic flex\n137: <div className=\"flex\" />\n138: <div className=\"flex flex-col\" />\n139: <div className=\"flex flex-row\" />\n140: \n141: // Alignment\n142: <div className=\"flex items-center\" />\n143: <div className=\"flex justify-center\" />\n144: <div className=\"flex justify-between\" />\n145: <div className=\"flex items-center justify-center\" />\n146: \n147: // Gap\n148: <div className=\"flex gap-4\" />\n149: <div className=\"flex flex-col gap-2\" />\n150: \n151: // Common pattern\n152: <div className=\"flex items-center justify-between gap-4\">\n153:   <span>Left</span>\n154:   <span>Right</span>\n155: </div>\n156: ```\n157: \n158: ### Grid\n159: \n160: ```typescript\n161: // Basic grid\n162: <div className=\"grid grid-cols-2 gap-4\" />\n163: <div className=\"grid grid-cols-3 gap-4\" />\n164: \n165: // Responsive columns\n166: <div className=\"grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-4\" />\n167: \n168: // Auto-fit columns\n169: <div className=\"grid grid-cols-[repeat(auto-fit,minmax(200px,1fr))] gap-4\" />\n170: ```\n171: \n172: ### Typography\n173: \n174: ```typescript\n175: // Font size\n176: <p className=\"text-sm\" />    // 14px\n177: <p className=\"text-base\" />  // 16px\n178: <p className=\"text-lg\" />    // 18px\n179: <p className=\"text-xl\" />    // 20px\n180: <p className=\"text-2xl\" />   // 24px\n181: <p className=\"text-3xl\" />   // 30px\n182: \n183: // Font weight\n184: <p className=\"font-normal\" />\n185: <p className=\"font-medium\" />\n186: <p className=\"font-semibold\" />\n187: <p className=\"font-bold\" />\n188: \n189: // Text color\n190: <p className=\"text-foreground\" />\n191: <p className=\"text-muted-foreground\" />\n192: <p className=\"text-primary\" />\n193: <p className=\"text-destructive\" />\n194: ```\n195: \n196: ### Sizing\n197: \n198: ```typescript\n199: // Width\n200: <div className=\"w-full\" />     // 100%\n201: <div className=\"w-1/2\" />      // 50%\n202: <div className=\"w-auto\" />\n203: <div className=\"max-w-md\" />   // max-width: 28rem\n204: <div className=\"max-w-lg\" />   // max-width: 32rem\n205: <div className=\"max-w-xl\" />   // max-width: 36rem\n206: \n207: // Height\n208: <div className=\"h-full\" />\n209: <div className=\"h-screen\" />   // 100vh\n210: <div className=\"min-h-screen\" />\n211: \n212: // Square\n213: <div className=\"size-4\" />     // 1rem x 1rem\n214: <div className=\"size-8\" />     // 2rem x 2rem\n215: ```\n216: \n217: ### Borders & Rounded\n218: \n219: ```typescript\n220: // Border\n221: <div className=\"border\" />\n222: <div className=\"border-2\" />\n223: <div className=\"border border-input\" />\n224: <div className=\"border-b\" />  // Bottom only\n225: \n226: // Rounded corners\n227: <div className=\"rounded\" />\n228: <div className=\"rounded-md\" />\n229: <div className=\"rounded-lg\" />\n230: <div className=\"rounded-full\" />\n231: ```\n232: \n233: ---\n234: \n235: ## Responsive Design\n236: \n237: ### Breakpoints\n238: \n239: ```typescript\n240: // Tailwind default breakpoints\n241: sm: 640px\n242: md: 768px\n243: lg: 1024px\n244: xl: 1280px\n245: 2xl: 1536px\n246: ```\n247: \n248: ### Mobile-First Approach\n249: \n250: ```typescript\n251: // Start with mobile, add breakpoints for larger\n252: <div className=\"\n253:   flex flex-col          // Mobile: column layout\n254:   md:flex-row            // Tablet+: row layout\n255:   gap-4\n256: \">\n257:   <div className=\"\n258:     w-full               // Mobile: full width\n259:     md:w-1/2             // Tablet+: half width\n260:   \">\n261:     Column 1\n262:   </div>\n263:   <div className=\"w-full md:w-1/2\">\n264:     Column 2\n265:   </div>\n266: </div>\n267: ```\n268: \n269: ### Common Responsive Patterns\n270: \n271: ```typescript\n272: // Responsive padding\n273: <div className=\"p-4 md:p-6 lg:p-8\" />\n274: \n275: // Responsive text\n276: <h1 className=\"text-2xl md:text-3xl lg:text-4xl\" />\n277: \n278: // Hide/show on screen sizes\n279: <div className=\"hidden md:block\" />  // Hidden on mobile, visible on tablet+\n280: <div className=\"md:hidden\" />        // Visible on mobile only\n281: \n282: // Responsive grid\n283: <div className=\"grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-4\" />\n284: ```\n285: \n286: ---\n287: \n288: ## Common Component Styling\n289: \n290: ### Card Pattern\n291: \n292: ```typescript\n293: <div className=\"rounded-lg border bg-card p-6 shadow-sm\">\n294:   <h3 className=\"text-lg font-semibold\">Title</h3>\n295:   <p className=\"text-muted-foreground\">Description</p>\n296: </div>\n297: ```\n298: \n299: ### Form Input Pattern\n300: \n301: ```typescript\n302: <div className=\"space-y-2\">\n303:   <label className=\"text-sm font-medium\">Label</label>\n304:   <input className=\"\n305:     flex h-9 w-full rounded-md border border-input bg-background\n306:     px-3 py-1 text-sm shadow-sm transition-colors\n307:     placeholder:text-muted-foreground\n308:     focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-1 focus-visible:ring-ring\n309:   \" />\n310: </div>\n311: ```\n312: \n313: ### Button Pattern\n314: \n315: ```typescript\n316: // Primary button\n317: <button className=\"\n318:   inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-md\n319:   bg-primary text-primary-foreground\n320:   h-9 px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium\n321:   hover:bg-primary/90\n322:   transition-colors\n323: \">\n324:   Button\n325: </button>\n326: \n327: // Outline button\n328: <button className=\"\n329:   border border-input bg-background\n330:   hover:bg-accent hover:text-accent-foreground\n331: \">\n332:   Outline\n333: </button>\n334: ```\n335: \n336: ### Page Layout Pattern\n337: \n338: ```typescript\n339: <div className=\"min-h-screen bg-background\">\n340:   <header className=\"border-b\">\n341:     <div className=\"container mx-auto px-4 py-4\">\n342:       Header\n343:     </div>\n344:   </header>\n345: \n346:   <main className=\"container mx-auto px-4 py-8\">\n347:     <h1 className=\"text-3xl font-bold mb-6\">Page Title</h1>\n348:     Content\n349:   </main>\n350: </div>\n351: ```\n352: \n353: ---\n354: \n355: ## Shadcn/UI Component Styling\n356: \n357: ### Customizing Shadcn Components\n358: \n359: ```typescript\n360: import { Button } from '~/components/ui/button';\n361: import { Card } from '~/components/ui/card';\n362: import { cn } from '~/lib/utils';\n363: \n364: // Add custom classes\n365: <Button className=\"w-full\">Full Width Button</Button>\n366: \n367: // Conditional classes\n368: <Button className={cn(\n369:   'w-full',\n370:   isLoading && 'opacity-50 cursor-not-allowed'\n371: )}>\n372:   Submit\n373: </Button>\n374: \n375: // Override padding\n376: <Card className=\"p-8\">More padding</Card>\n377: ```\n378: \n379: ### CVA Variants\n380: \n381: Shadcn/UI components use CVA (Class Variance Authority) for variants:\n382: \n383: ```typescript\n384: // Button variants\n385: <Button variant=\"default\">Primary</Button>\n386: <Button variant=\"secondary\">Secondary</Button>\n387: <Button variant=\"destructive\">Danger</Button>\n388: <Button variant=\"outline\">Outlined</Button>\n389: <Button variant=\"ghost\">Ghost</Button>\n390: <Button variant=\"link\">Link</Button>\n391: \n392: // Sizes\n393: <Button size=\"sm\">Small</Button>\n394: <Button size=\"default\">Default</Button>\n395: <Button size=\"lg\">Large</Button>\n396: <Button size=\"icon\"><Icon /></Button>\n397: \n398: // Input variants\n399: <Input variant=\"default\" />       // Standard border + indigo focus\n400: <Input variant=\"error\" />         // Red border + red focus ring\n401: \n402: // Select variants\n403: <Select variant=\"default\" />      // Standard filter select\n404: <Select variant=\"compact\" />      // Pagination row selector\n405: <Select variant=\"ghost\" />        // Transparent status dropdown\n406: ```\n407: \n408: ### Variant-First Styling Rule (MANDATORY)\n409: \n410: **This rule applies to ALL reusable components — not just UI primitives.**\n411: \n412: When any reusable component needs visually distinct styles across different call sites, the difference **MUST** be expressed as a cva variant on the component — never as duplicated `className` strings at call sites.\n413: \n414: **Rules:**\n415: 1. Every reusable component **MUST** accept a `className` prop for one-off layout overrides\n416: 2. When the same styling pattern appears at 2+ call sites, it **MUST** be extracted as a cva variant\n417: 3. Semantic states (error, success, warning, loading) **MUST** always be variants, even if used at only 1 call site\n418: 4. `className` is reserved for **one-off, context-specific overrides** (width, height, spacing, positioning)\n419: \n420: | Pattern | Approach | Example |\n421: |---------|----------|---------|\n422: | Error/invalid state | **Variant** | `<Input variant=\"error\" />` |\n423: | Compact/dense layout | **Variant** | `<Select variant=\"compact\" />` |\n424: | Ghost/transparent style | **Variant** | `<Select variant=\"ghost\" />` |\n425: | Any repeated style group | **Variant** | Extract to cva if used 2+ times |\n426: | Icon offset padding | className | `className=\"pl-10\"` |\n427: | Full-width override | className | `className=\"w-full\"` |\n428: | Context-specific height | className | `className=\"h-24\"` |\n429: | Dynamic status color | className | `className={style.text}` |\n430: \n431: **Anti-patterns to reject:**\n432: - Duplicated Tailwind class groups at multiple call sites — extract a cva variant\n433: - Raw `<select>` / `<input>` / `<textarea>` / `<button>` with inline Tailwind — use the UI primitive with variant + className\n434: - Reusable component without `className` prop — every reusable component must accept className\n435: - Creating a new component for a different style of an existing component — add a variant instead\n436: \n437: ---\n438: \n439: ## What NOT to Do\n440: \n441: ### Avoid Inline Style Objects\n442: \n443: ```typescript\n444: // ❌ AVOID - Inline style objects\n445: <div style={{ padding: '16px', marginBottom: '12px' }}>\n446:   Content\n447: </div>\n448: \n449: // ✅ PREFERRED - Tailwind classes\n450: <div className=\"p-4 mb-3\">\n451:   Content\n452: </div>\n453: ```\n454: \n455: ### Avoid CSS-in-JS Libraries\n456: \n457: ```typescript\n458: // ❌ AVOID - styled-components, emotion, etc.\n459: import styled from 'styled-components';\n460: \n461: const StyledDiv = styled.div`\n462:   padding: 16px;\n463: `;\n464: \n465: // ✅ PREFERRED - Tailwind utility classes\n466: <div className=\"p-4\">Content</div>\n467: ```\n468: \n469: ### Avoid Global CSS (except for themes)\n470: \n471: ```typescript\n472: // ❌ AVOID - Custom CSS classes in separate files\n473: // styles.css\n474: .my-custom-button { padding: 16px; }\n475: \n476: // ✅ PREFERRED - Tailwind classes or CVA variants\n477: <Button className=\"px-4\">Button</Button>\n478: ```\n479: \n480: ---\n481: \n482: ## Summary\n483: \n484: **Styling Checklist:**\n485: \n486: - ✅ Use Tailwind CSS utility classes directly\n487: - ✅ Use `cn()` for conditional class merging\n488: - ✅ Use semantic color variables (`bg-background`, `text-foreground`)\n489: - ✅ Mobile-first responsive design\n490: - ✅ Shadcn/UI component variants via CVA\n491: - ✅ Dark mode via CSS variables (automatic)\n492: - ❌ No inline style objects\n493: - ❌ No CSS-in-JS libraries\n494: - ❌ No custom CSS files (except themes)\n495: \n496: **See Also:**\n497: \n498: - [component-patterns.md](component-patterns.md) - Component structure\n499: - [complete-examples.md](complete-examples.md) - Full styling examples\n\n(End of file - total 499 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Styling Guide\n\nModern styling patterns using Tailwind CSS 4, Shadcn/UI, and CSS variables.\n\n---\n\n## Core Concepts\n\n### Tailwind CSS 4\n\nThe project uses Tailwind CSS 4 with utility-first styling:\n\n```typescript\n// Direct utility classes\n<div className=\"p-4 mb-3 flex flex-col gap-2\">\n  Content\n</div>\n```\n\n### cn() Utility","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".claude/react/docs/styling-guide.md","time":{"start":1779192378974,"end":1779192379256}},"id":"prt_e402131090012l29BQbOasvy3b","sessionID":"ses_1bfdeff9cffel20XYIHhGhKvJ3","messageID":"msg_e4021040c0013iNRwEANypdde1"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1779192380999,"sessionID":"ses_1bfdeff9cffel20XYIHhGhKvJ3","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_03_q9xoj4BNVAY1k69C0LMi2216","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude/react/docs/file-organization.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude/react/docs/file-organization.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # File Organization\n2: \n3: Proper file and directory structure for maintainable, scalable frontend code.\n4: \n5: ---\n6: \n7: ## CRITICAL RULES CHECKLIST\n8: \n9: Before implementing any feature, verify:\n10: \n11: ### Directory Structure\n12: \n13: - [ ] Components placed in correct directory:\n14:   - `components/ui/` - ONLY Shadcn/UI primitives (lowercase names)\n15:   - `components/atoms/` - Custom reusable atomic components (PascalCase, non-Shadcn)\n16:   - `components/modals/` - All modal/dialog overlay components (PascalCase, Modal suffix)\n17:   - `components/shared/` - Feature-specific shared components (Navbar, Sidebar, Breadcrumb, PinMarker)\n18:   - `components/layouts/` - Layout wrappers only\n19:   - `components/guards/` - Route guards\n20:   - `pages/` - Page components by route hierarchy\n21: - [ ] Services organized properly:\n22:   - `services/httpService.ts` - Axios orchestrator (do not modify)\n23:   - `services/httpMethods/` - HTTP factories (do not modify)\n24:   - `services/httpServices/` - Domain-specific services\n25:   - `services/httpServices/` - Contains `createAsyncThunk` for READ ops + plain methods for mutations\n26: \n27: ### Naming Conventions\n28: \n29: - [ ] Components use PascalCase: `UserCard.tsx`, `Button.tsx`\n30: - [ ] Shadcn/UI components use lowercase: `button.tsx`, `card.tsx`\n31: - [ ] Services use camelCase + Service: `userService.ts`\n32: - [ ] Routes use kebab-case: `auth.routes.ts`\n33: - [ ] Redux slices use camelCase + Slice: `userSlice.ts`\n34: \n35: ### Import Rules\n36: \n37: - [ ] Using `~/` alias for all imports (not relative paths like `../../`)\n38: - [ ] Import order follows standard:\n39:   1. React and React-related\n40:   2. Third-party libraries\n41:   3. Redux hooks and actions\n42:   4. Components\n43:   5. Utilities\n44:   6. Type imports (grouped)\n45:   7. Relative imports (same feature only)\n46: - [ ] All imports use single quotes (project standard)\n47: \n48: ### New Feature Requirements\n49: \n50: When creating a new feature, you MUST create these files:\n51: \n52: - [ ] `app/pages/{feature}/index.tsx` - Main page component\n53: - [ ] `app/services/httpServices/{feature}Service.ts` - API service\n54: - [ ] `app/services/httpServices/queries/use{Feature}.ts` - Query hooks (if public page)\n55: - [ ] `app/redux/features/{feature}Slice.ts` - Redux slice (if needed)\n56: - [ ] `app/types/{feature}.d.ts` - TypeScript types\n57: - [ ] `app/routes/{feature}.routes.ts` - Route definitions\n58: - [ ] `app/utils/validations/{feature}.ts` - Zod schemas (if forms needed)\n59: \n60: Then update:\n61: \n62: - [ ] `app/routes.ts` - Import and add new routes\n63: - [ ] `app/redux/store/rootReducer.ts` - Add reducer (if using Redux)\n64: - [ ] `app/services/httpServices/queries/index.ts` - Export query hooks (if created)\n65: \n66: ---\n67: \n68: ## PRE-IMPLEMENTATION VERIFICATION\n69: \n70: Before writing ANY code, answer these questions:\n71: \n72: **Component Placement:**\n73: \n74: 1. Is this a Shadcn/UI primitive? → Goes in `components/ui/` with lowercase name\n75: 2. Is this a modal/dialog overlay? → Goes in `components/modals/` with PascalCase and `Modal` suffix\n76: 3. Is this a small, reusable, non-Shadcn component (badge, spinner, card, dropdown)? → Goes in `components/atoms/` with PascalCase\n77: 4. Is this coupled to a specific layout area (navbar, sidebar, breadcrumb)? → Goes in `components/shared/`\n78: 5. Is this a layout wrapper? → Goes in `components/layouts/` with PascalCase\n79: 6. Is this a route guard? → Goes in `components/guards/` with PascalCase\n80: 7. Is this a page component? → Goes in `pages/{route-area}/` with PascalCase\n81: 8. **NEVER** define reusable components inline inside page files — extract to the correct folder\n82: \n83: **Service Layer:**\n84: \n85: 1. Am I modifying httpService.ts? → STOP - Do not modify the orchestrator\n86: 2. Am I creating a new API service? → Goes in `services/httpServices/`\n87: 3. Is this for a public page? → Create query hook in `services/httpServices/queries/`\n88: 4. Does this need server-side data? → Use React Router server actions in `utils/actions/`\n89: \n90: **Imports:**\n91: \n92: 1. Am I using relative paths like `../../../`? → STOP - Use `~/` alias instead\n93: 2. Are my imports organized by category? → Follow the import order standard\n94: 3. Am I using double quotes? → STOP - Use single quotes (project standard)\n95: \n96: **New Feature:**\n97: \n98: 1. Have I created ALL 7 required file types? → See \"New Feature Requirements\" checklist\n99: 2. Have I updated the 3 integration points? → routes.ts, rootReducer.ts, queries/index.ts\n100: 3. Does the feature name match across all files? → Verify consistent naming\n101: \n102: ---\n103: \n104: ## Directory Structure\n105: \n106: > **Note:** React Router 7 framework mode uses `app/` as the default directory (not `src/`). This is configured in `react-router.config.ts` via `appDirectory: \"app\"`.\n107: \n108: ```\n109: app/                              # React Router 7 app directory (NOT src/)\n110: ├── components/\n111: │   ├── ui/                       # Shadcn/UI primitives (lowercase)\n112: │   │   ├── button.tsx\n113: │   │   ├── input.tsx\n114: │   │   ├── card.tsx\n115: │   │   └── form.tsx\n116: │   ├── atoms/                    # Custom reusable atomic components (PascalCase)\n117: │   │   ├── StatusBadge.tsx\n118: │   │   ├── LoadingSpinner.tsx\n119: │   │   ├── EmptyState.tsx\n120: │   │   └── FeedbackCard.tsx\n121: │   ├── modals/                   # Modal/dialog overlay components (PascalCase)\n122: │   │   ├── ConfirmModal.tsx\n123: │   │   └── ViewReplyModal.tsx\n124: │   ├── shared/                   # Feature-specific shared components\n125: │   │   ├── AdminSidebar.tsx\n126: │   │   ├── ClientNavbar.tsx\n127: │   │   └── Breadcrumb.tsx\n128: │   ├── layouts/                  # Layout wrappers\n129: │   │   └── ProtectedLayout.tsx   # Inline auth + RBAC (recommended pattern)\n130: │   └── guards/                   # Route guards\n131: │       ├── GuestGuard.tsx        # Auth pages — renders <Outlet /> for guests\n132: │       ├── AuthGuard.tsx         # One-off auth check (optional)\n133: │       └── RoleGuard.tsx         # One-off role check (optional)\n134: ├── contexts/                     # React Context providers\n135: │   └── AuthContext.tsx           # Auth state + useAuth() hook\n136: ├── enums/                        # Enum definitions\n137: │   ├── role.enum.ts              # Synced from backend\n138: │   ├── sort-order.enum.ts        # Frontend-only\n139: │   └── index.ts                  # Barrel export\n140: ├── hooks/                        # Custom hooks\n141: │   ├── useAuth.ts                # Auth state hook (or re-export from contexts/)\n142: │   └── providers/                # Context providers\n143: │       └── providers.tsx         # Redux provider setup\n144: ├── lib/                          # Utilities\n145: │   └── utils.ts                  # cn() utility\n146: ├── pages/                        # Page components\n147: │   ├── redirect-home.tsx         # Root redirect (SPA: <Navigate>, SSR: loader)\n148: │   ├── not-found.tsx             # 404 catch-all page\n149: │   ├── unauthorized.tsx          # 403 unauthorized page\n150: │   ├── auth/                     # Auth pages (wrapped by GuestGuard layout)\n151: │   │   ├── layout.tsx            # Delegates to <GuestGuard />\n152: │   │   ├── LoginPage.tsx\n153: │   │   └── RegisterPage.tsx\n154: │   └── protected/                # Protected pages (wrapped by ProtectedLayout)\n155: │       ├── dashboard.tsx\n156: │       ├── users.tsx\n157: │       └── settings.tsx\n158: ├── redux/                        # State management (if using Redux)\n159: │   ├── features/                 # Redux slices\n160: │   │   ├── authSlice.ts          # Auth state (alternative to AuthContext)\n161: │   │   └── userSlice.ts\n162: │   └── store/                    # Store configuration\n163: │       ├── store.ts\n164: │       ├── rootReducer.ts\n165: │       └── hooks.ts              # useAppDispatch, useAppSelector\n166: ├── routes/                       # Route definitions (declarative config)\n167: │   ├── auth.routes.ts            # Auth routes (login, register)\n168: │   └── protected.routes.ts       # Protected routes (RouteConfigEntry)\n169: ├── services/                     # API services\n170: │   ├── api/                      # Axios instance and config\n171: │   │   └── axios.ts              # Axios with interceptors (401 refresh)\n172: │   ├── httpService.ts            # Axios orchestrator (legacy)\n173: │   ├── httpMethods/              # HTTP method factories\n174: │   │   ├── index.ts\n175: │   │   ├── get.ts\n176: │   │   ├── post.ts\n177: │   │   └── responseInterceptor.ts\n178: │   └── httpServices/             # Domain-specific services\n179: │       ├── *Service.ts           # Domain services with createAsyncThunk for READ ops\n180: │       │   └── index.ts\n181: │       ├── authService.ts\n182: │       ├── userService.ts\n183: │       └── itemService.ts\n184: ├── styles/                       # CSS files\n185: │   └── app.css                   # Tailwind + theme variables\n186: ├── types/                        # TypeScript types\n187: │   ├── user.d.ts\n188: │   └── httpService.d.ts\n189: ├── utils/                        # Utility functions\n190: │   ├── errorHandler.ts\n191: │   ├── actions/                  # Server actions (SSR mode only)\n192: │   └── validations/              # Zod schemas\n193: │       └── auth.ts\n194: ├── root.tsx                      # App root (replaces main.tsx + index.html + App.tsx)\n195: └── routes.ts                     # Main route config (declarative, no JSX <Route>)\n196: \n197: # Project root files (outside app/)\n198: ├── react-router.config.ts        # RR7 config (ssr: true/false, appDirectory)\n199: ├── vite.config.ts                # Vite config with @react-router/dev/vite plugin\n200: ├── tsconfig.json                 # TypeScript config (includes .react-router/types)\n201: └── .react-router/                # Auto-generated types (gitignored)\n202:     └── types/\n203: ```\n204: \n205: ---\n206: \n207: ## Folder Purposes\n208: \n209: ### components/\n210: \n211: Reusable components organized by type:\n212: \n213: ```\n214: components/\n215: ├── ui/                  # Shadcn/UI primitives (lowercase names)\n216: ├── atoms/               # Custom reusable atomic components (PascalCase)\n217: ├── modals/              # Modal/dialog overlay components (PascalCase, Modal suffix)\n218: ├── shared/              # Feature-specific shared components (Navbar, Sidebar, Breadcrumb)\n219: ├── layouts/             # Layout wrappers\n220: └── guards/              # Route guards\n221: ```\n222: \n223: **Rules:**\n224: \n225: - `ui/` — Shadcn/UI primitives only (lowercase filenames)\n226: - `atoms/` — Small, reusable custom components not from Shadcn (badges, spinners, dropdowns, cards)\n227: - `modals/` — All modal/dialog overlay components (use `Modal` suffix in name)\n228: - `shared/` — Components coupled to a specific layout area (navbar, sidebar, breadcrumb, pin marker)\n229: - `layouts/` — Page layout wrappers\n230: - `guards/` — Route access guards\n231: - **NEVER** define reusable sub-components inline inside page files — extract to the correct folder\n232: \n233: ---\n234: \n235: ### pages/\n236: \n237: Page components organized by route area:\n238: \n239: ```\n240: pages/\n241: ├── layout.tsx           # Main layout wrapper\n242: ├── auth/                # Authentication-related pages\n243: │   ├── layout.tsx       # Auth-specific layout\n244: │   ├── login.tsx\n245: │   └── register.tsx\n246: └── public/              # Public pages\n247:     ├── home.tsx\n248:     └── about.tsx\n249: ```\n250: \n251: **Rules:**\n252: \n253: - Each page is a default export\n254: - Layout files wrap child routes\n255: - Organize by route hierarchy\n256: \n257: ---\n258: \n259: ### redux/\n260: \n261: Redux state management:\n262: \n263: ```\n264: redux/\n265: ├── features/            # Redux slices by domain\n266: │   ├── userSlice.ts\n267: │   └── counterSlice.ts\n268: └── store/               # Store configuration\n269:     ├── store.ts         # Store setup\n270:     ├── rootReducer.ts   # Combined reducers\n271:     └── hooks.ts         # Typed hooks (useAppDispatch, useAppSelector)\n272: ```\n273: \n274: **Rules:**\n275: \n276: - One slice per domain/feature\n277: - Async thunks defined in service files, not slices\n278: - Always use typed hooks from `store/hooks.ts`\n279: \n280: ---\n281: \n282: ### services/\n283: \n284: API services and HTTP client:\n285: \n286: ```\n287: services/\n288: ├── httpService.ts         # Axios orchestrator\n289: ├── httpMethods/           # HTTP method factories\n290: │   ├── index.ts           # Export all methods\n291: │   ├── get.ts             # GET factory\n292: │   ├── post.ts            # POST factory\n293: │   ├── put.ts             # PUT factory\n294: │   ├── delete.ts          # DELETE factory\n295: │   ├── patch.ts           # PATCH factory\n296: │   ├── requestInterceptor.ts   # Request interceptor\n297: │   └── responseInterceptor.ts  # Response interceptor\n298: └── httpServices/          # Domain-specific services\n299:     ├── *Service.ts        # Domain services with createAsyncThunk for READ ops\n300:     │   ├── index.ts\n301:     │   └── usePublicCategories.ts\n302:     ├── authService.ts\n303:     ├── userService.ts\n304:     └── itemService.ts\n305: ```\n306: \n307: **Rules:**\n308: \n309: - `httpService.ts` is the Axios orchestrator with interceptors\n310: - `httpMethods/` contains factory functions for each HTTP method\n311: - `httpServices/` contains domain-specific API services\n312: - Each service file contains `createAsyncThunk` exports for READ operations and plain methods for mutations\n313: - Feature services use `httpService` for all requests\n314: \n315: ---\n316: \n317: ### types/\n318: \n319: TypeScript type definitions organized by domain:\n320: \n321: ```\n322: types/\n323: ├── {domain}.d.ts        # One file per domain (e.g., user.d.ts, animal.d.ts)\n324: ├── common.d.ts          # Shared utility types (e.g., PaginatedResponse)\n325: ├── components.d.ts      # Shared component prop interfaces\n326: ├── layout.d.ts          # Layout component prop interfaces\n327: ├── httpService.d.ts     # API response/error types\n328: └── index.ts             # Barrel re-export (all domain files)\n329: ```\n330: \n331: **Rules:**\n332: \n333: - Use `.d.ts` extension for type-only files\n334: - One `.d.ts` file per domain — group entity + related props together\n335: - Barrel `index.ts` re-exports all domain files for `~/types` imports\n336: - Cross-domain imports use relative paths (e.g., `import type { User } from './user'`)\n337: - No monolithic type files — keep `index.ts` as re-exports only\n338: - **Redux `*State` interfaces MUST be in `~/types/{domain}.d.ts`** — NEVER declare inline in slice files\n339: - **Domain types (entities, rows, summaries) MUST be in `~/types/{domain}.d.ts`** — NEVER declare inline in components/pages\n340: - **API request/response types (query params, create/update payloads, dashboard DTOs) MUST be in `~/types/{domain}.d.ts`** — NEVER declare inline in service files (`services/httpServices/`)\n341: - **Only component Props interfaces and local UI unions (`FilterType`, `SortType`) may stay inline** in component files\n342: \n343: ---\n344: \n345: ### utils/\n346: \n347: Utility functions:\n348: \n349: ```\n350: utils/\n351: ├── errorHandler.ts      # HTTP error handling\n352: ├── actions/             # React Router server actions\n353: │   └── auth.ts\n354: └── validations/         # Zod validation schemas\n355:     └── auth.ts\n356: ```\n357: \n358: **Rules:**\n359: \n360: - Pure utility functions (no React hooks)\n361: - Validation schemas use Zod\n362: - Server actions for form submissions\n363: \n364: ---\n365: \n366: ### enums/\n367: \n368: Enum definitions synced from backend and frontend-only enums:\n369: \n370: ```\n371: enums/\n372: ├── role.enum.ts             # Synced from backend\n373: ├── pin-status.enum.ts       # Synced from backend\n374: ├── screen-status.enum.ts    # Synced from backend\n375: ├── sort-order.enum.ts       # Frontend-only\n376: └── index.ts                 # Barrel export\n377: ```\n378: \n379: **Rules:**\n380: \n381: - Backend enums are mirrored exactly from `backend/src/shared/enums/`\n382: - Frontend-only enums for UI-specific values also live here\n383: - All enums use PascalCase with `Enum` suffix\n384: - File names use kebab-case with `.enum.ts` extension\n385: - Barrel `index.ts` re-exports all enums\n386: - Import via `~/enums` (not individual files)\n387: - Run `/sync-enums` when backend adds/modifies enums\n388: - When enum values change, update ALL references (comparisons, Record keys, option values, useState defaults, function arguments, JSX attributes)\n389: \n390: ---\n391: \n392: ### hooks/\n393: \n394: Custom React hooks:\n395: \n396: ```\n397: hooks/\n398: └── providers/           # Context providers\n399:     └── providers.tsx    # Redux provider setup\n400: ```\n401: \n402: **Rules:**\n403: \n404: - Custom hooks that use React hooks\n405: - Provider setup for context\n406: \n407: ---\n408: \n409: ### routes/\n410: \n411: Route configuration files (React Router 7 declarative config):\n412: \n413: ```\n414: routes/\n415: ├── auth.routes.ts           # Auth routes (login, register, forgot-password)\n416: ├── protected.routes.ts      # Protected routes (RouteConfigEntry with layout wrapper)\n417: └── public.routes.ts         # Public routes (optional)\n418: ```\n419: \n420: **Rules:**\n421: \n422: - Separate files for route groups\n423: - Use `route()`, `layout()`, `index()` from `@react-router/dev/routes`\n424: - Protected routes use `RouteConfigEntry` type (single layout wrapper)\n425: - Auth routes are an array (wrapped by auth layout in `routes.ts`)\n426: - All imported into main `routes.ts`\n427: \n428: **Route Config Pattern:**\n429: \n430: ```typescript\n431: // ~/routes/protected.routes.ts\n432: import { type RouteConfigEntry, route, layout } from \"@react-router/dev/routes\";\n433: \n434: export const protectedRoutes: RouteConfigEntry = layout(\n435:   \"components/layouts/ProtectedLayout.tsx\",\n436:   [\n437:     route(\"dashboard\", \"pages/protected/dashboard.tsx\"),\n438:     route(\"users\", \"pages/protected/users.tsx\"),\n439:     route(\"unauthorized\", \"pages/unauthorized.tsx\"),\n440:   ],\n441: );\n442: ```\n443: \n444: ---\n445: \n446: ## Import Alias\n447: \n448: The project uses `~/` as an alias for the `/app/` directory:\n449: \n450: ```typescript\n451: // tsconfig.json\n452: {\n453:   \"compilerOptions\": {\n454:     \"paths\": {\n455:       \"~/*\": [\"./app/*\"]\n456:     }\n457:   }\n458: }\n459: ```\n460: \n461: **Examples:**\n462: \n463: ```typescript\n464: // ✅ Correct - using alias\n465: import { Button } from \"~/components/ui/button\";\n466: import { useAppDispatch } from \"~/redux/store/hooks\";\n467: import type { User } from \"~/types/user\";\n468: \n469: // ❌ Avoid - relative paths for distant imports\n470: import { Button } from \"../../../components/ui/button\";\n471: ```\n472: \n473: ---\n474: \n475: ## File Naming Conventions\n476: \n477: | Type         | Convention          | Example                      |\n478: | ------------ | ------------------- | ---------------------------- |\n479: | Components   | PascalCase          | `Button.tsx`, `UserCard.tsx` |\n480: | Shadcn/UI    | lowercase           | `button.tsx`, `card.tsx`     |\n481: | Redux slices | camelCase + Slice   | `userSlice.ts`               |\n482: | Services     | camelCase + Service | `userService.ts`             |\n483: | Types        | camelCase           | `user.d.ts`                  |\n484: | Utils        | camelCase           | `errorHandler.ts`            |\n485: | Routes       | kebab-case          | `auth.routes.ts`             |\n486: | Validations  | camelCase           | `auth.ts`                    |\n487: \n488: ---\n489: \n490: ## Creating a New Feature - MANDATORY CHECKLIST\n491: \n492: When adding a new feature (e.g., \"posts\"), you MUST create these files in this order:\n493: \n494: ### PHASE 1: Type Definitions\n495: \n496: ```\n497: app/types/\n498: └── post.d.ts              # TypeScript types\n499: ```\n500: \n501: **Verify:** Types exported and available for import\n502: \n503: ### PHASE 2: API Service Layer\n504: \n505: ```\n506: app/services/httpServices/\n507: ├── postService.ts         # API service using httpService\n508: └── postService.ts         # createAsyncThunk for fetchPosts + plain methods for create/update/delete\n509: ```\n510: \n511: **Verify:** Service uses httpService methods, not raw axios\n512: \n513: ### PHASE 3: State Management (If Needed)\n514: \n515: ```\n516: app/redux/features/\n517: └── postSlice.ts           # Redux slice (if global state needed)\n518: ```\n519: \n520: **Verify:** Slice uses types from step 1, async logic in service layer\n521: \n522: ### PHASE 4: Pages & Routes\n523: \n524: ```\n525: app/pages/posts/\n526: ├── index.tsx              # Main page component\n527: app/routes/\n528: └── post.routes.ts         # Route definitions\n529: ```\n530: \n531: **Verify:** Page uses proper imports with `~/` alias\n532: \n533: ### PHASE 5: Validation (If Forms)\n534: \n535: ```\n536: app/utils/validations/\n537: └── post.ts                # Zod schemas (if forms needed)\n538: ```\n539: \n540: **Verify:** Schemas match type definitions\n541: \n542: ### PHASE 6: Integration (CRITICAL - DO NOT SKIP)\n543: \n544: Update these files:\n545: \n546: ```\n547: ✓ app/routes.ts\n548:   - Import: import { postRoutes } from './routes/post.routes';\n549:   - Add to routes array\n550: \n551: ✓ app/redux/store/rootReducer.ts (if using Redux)\n552:   - Import: import postReducer from '../features/postSlice';\n553:   - Add to combineReducers: post: postReducer\n554: \n555: ✓ app/services/httpServices/queries/index.ts (if created queries)\n556:   - Export: export * from './usePosts';\n557: ```\n558: \n559: ### VERIFICATION BEFORE COMMIT\n560: \n561: Run these checks:\n562: \n563: - [ ] All 7 file types created (or explicitly decided not needed)\n564: - [ ] All 3 integration points updated\n565: - [ ] All imports use `~/` alias\n566: - [ ] All naming conventions followed\n567: - [ ] TypeScript compiles: `npm run typecheck`\n568: - [ ] Build succeeds: `npm run build`\n569: \n570: **FAILURE TO FOLLOW THIS CHECKLIST WILL RESULT IN BROKEN IMPORTS AND TYPE ERRORS.**\n571: \n572: ---\n573: \n574: ## Import Organization\n575: \n576: ### Import Order (Recommended)\n577: \n578: ```typescript\n579: // 1. React and React-related\n580: import { useState, useCallback, useMemo } from \"react\";\n581: \n582: // 2. Third-party libraries\n583: import { useForm } from \"react-hook-form\";\n584: import { zodResolver } from \"@hookform/resolvers/zod\";\n585: import { Link, useNavigate } from \"react-router\";\n586: \n587: // 3. Redux hooks and actions\n588: import { useAppDispatch, useAppSelector } from \"~/redux/store/hooks\";\n589: import { someAction } from \"~/redux/features/someSlice\";\n590: \n591: // 3.5 Enums\n592: import { RolesEnum, PinStatusEnum } from \"~/enums\";\n593: \n594: // 4. Components\n595: import { Button } from \"~/components/ui/button\";\n596: import { Card } from \"~/components/ui/card\";\n597: \n598: // 5. Utilities\n599: import { cn } from \"~/lib/utils\";\n600: import { httpService } from \"~/services/httpService\";\n601: \n602: // 6. Type imports (grouped)\n603: import type { User } from \"~/types/user\";\n604: import type { Post } from \"~/types/post\";\n605: \n606: // 7. Relative imports (same feature)\n607: import { MySubComponent } from \"./MySubComponent\";\n608: ```\n609: \n610: **Use single quotes** for all imports (project standard)\n611: \n612: ---\n613: \n614: ## Summary\n615: \n616: | Directory                 | Purpose                                                                  |\n617: | ------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------ |\n618: | `components/ui/`          | Shadcn/UI primitives (lowercase)                                         |\n619: | `components/atoms/`       | Custom reusable atomic components (badges, spinners, small interactives) |\n620: | `components/modals/`      | Modal/dialog overlay components                                          |\n621: | `components/shared/`      | Feature-specific shared components (Navbar, Sidebar, Breadcrumb)         |\n622: | `components/layouts/`     | Layout wrappers                                                          |\n623: | `components/guards/`      | Route guards                                                             |\n624: | `pages/`                  | Page components by route                                                 |\n625: | `redux/features/`         | Redux slices                                                             |\n626: | `redux/store/`            | Store configuration                                                      |\n627: | `services/httpService.ts` | Axios orchestrator                                                       |\n628: | `services/httpMethods/`   | HTTP method factories                                                    |\n629: | `services/httpServices/`  | Domain-specific API services                                             |\n630: | `redux/features/`         | Redux slices with extraReducers for thunks                               |\n631: | `types/`                  | TypeScript types                                                         |\n632: | `enums/`                  | Enum definitions (synced from backend + frontend-only)                   |\n633: | `utils/`                  | Utility functions                                                        |\n634: | `utils/validations/`      | Zod schemas                                                              |\n635: | `routes/`                 | Route definitions                                                        |\n636: | `hooks/`                  | Custom hooks                                                             |\n637: | `lib/`                    | Utility libraries (`cn()`)                                               |\n638: | `styles/`                 | CSS files                                                                |\n639: \n640: ---\n641: \n642: ## Related Resources\n643: \n644: - [Component Patterns](component-patterns.md) - How to structure components\n645: - [Data Fetching](data-fetching.md) - Service layer patterns\n646: - [Routing Guide](routing-guide.md) - Route organization\n\n(End of file - total 646 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# File Organization\n\nProper file and directory structure for maintainable, scalable frontend code.\n\n---\n\n## CRITICAL RULES CHECKLIST\n\nBefore implementing any feature, verify:\n\n### Directory Structure\n\n- [ ] Components placed in correct directory:\n  - `components/ui/` - ONLY Shadcn/UI primitives (lowercase names)\n  - `components/atoms/` - Custom reusable atomic components (PascalCase, non-Shadcn)\n  - `components/modals/` - All modal/dialog overlay components (PascalCase, Modal suffix)\n  - `components/shared/` - Feature-specific shared components (Navbar, Sidebar, Breadcrumb, PinMarker)\n  - `components/layouts/` - Layout wrappers only\n  - `components/guards/` - Route guards\n  - `pages/` - Page components by route hierarchy","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".claude/react/docs/file-organization.md","time":{"start":1779192380707,"end":1779192380998}},"id":"prt_e402137e7001a5Wib0ixeL3Kcf","sessionID":"ses_1bfdeff9cffel20XYIHhGhKvJ3","messageID":"msg_e4021040c0013iNRwEANypdde1"}}
