{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1779192391065,"sessionID":"ses_1bfdeff9cffel20XYIHhGhKvJ3","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"glob","callID":"call_01_uEJS2A530SzKgPk8A8LB7048","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"frontend/app/pages/**/*.tsx"},"output":"/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/frontend/app/pages/admin/users.tsx\n/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/frontend/app/pages/admin/inquiries.tsx\n/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/frontend/app/pages/admin/property-form.tsx\n/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/frontend/app/pages/admin/properties.tsx\n/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/frontend/app/pages/admin/dashboard.tsx\n/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/frontend/app/pages/profile.tsx\n/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/frontend/app/pages/renter/inquiries.tsx\n/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/frontend/app/pages/renter/favorites.tsx\n/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/frontend/app/pages/renter/detail.tsx\n/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/frontend/app/pages/renter/search.tsx\n/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/frontend/app/pages/auth/admin-login.tsx\n/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/frontend/app/pages/auth/reset-password.tsx\n/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/frontend/app/pages/auth/forgot-password.tsx\n/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/frontend/app/pages/auth/layout.tsx\n/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/frontend/app/pages/unauthorized.tsx\n/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/frontend/app/pages/not-found.tsx\n/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/frontend/app/pages/redirect-home.tsx\n/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/frontend/app/pages/layout.tsx\n/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/frontend/app/pages/auth/register.tsx\n/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/frontend/app/pages/auth/login.tsx","metadata":{"count":20,"truncated":false},"title":"","time":{"start":1779192390765,"end":1779192391064}},"id":"prt_e4021615a001YMUXCLBHMDHs5V","sessionID":"ses_1bfdeff9cffel20XYIHhGhKvJ3","messageID":"msg_e40213fe2001selwtPtEjGbkJE"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1779192392669,"sessionID":"ses_1bfdeff9cffel20XYIHhGhKvJ3","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_02_SrvAccJIYNC3p1j9HjON8057","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude/react/docs/best-practices.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude/react/docs/best-practices.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Frontend Best Practices\n2: \n3: ## React Component Best Practices\n4: \n5: ### Component File Organization\n6: \n7: ```typescript\n8: // GOOD: Component with typed props, hooks at top\n9: interface ButtonProps {\n10:     variant?: 'primary' | 'outline';\n11:     children: React.ReactNode;\n12:     onClick?: () => void;\n13:     disabled?: boolean;\n14: }\n15: \n16: export function Button({ variant = 'primary', children, onClick, disabled }: ButtonProps) {\n17:     const { t } = useTranslation();\n18:     const [isLoading, setIsLoading] = useState(false);\n19: \n20:     const handleClick = () => {\n21:         if (onClick) onClick();\n22:     };\n23: \n24:     return (\n25:         <button\n26:             className={cn(\n27:                 'px-4 py-2 rounded-md',\n28:                 variant === 'primary' && 'bg-blue-500 text-white',\n29:                 variant === 'outline' && 'border border-gray-300',\n30:                 disabled && 'opacity-50 cursor-not-allowed'\n31:             )}\n32:             onClick={handleClick}\n33:             disabled={disabled || isLoading}\n34:         >\n35:             {children}\n36:         </button>\n37:     );\n38: }\n39: \n40: // BAD: Untyped props, inline styles, logic in JSX\n41: export function Button(props) {\n42:     return (\n43:         <button style={{ padding: '10px' }} onClick={() => props.onClick && props.onClick()}>\n44:             {props.children}\n45:         </button>\n46:     );\n47: }\n48: ```\n49: \n50: ### Component Organization Pattern\n51: \n52: ```\n53: components/\n54: ├── ui/          # Shadcn/UI primitives (lowercase)\n55: ├── atoms/       # Custom reusable atomic components (PascalCase)\n56: ├── modals/      # Modal/dialog overlays (PascalCase, Modal suffix)\n57: ├── shared/      # Feature-specific shared components (Navbar, Sidebar, Breadcrumb)\n58: ├── layouts/     # Layout wrappers\n59: └── guards/      # Route guards\n60: ```\n61: \n62: ### Component Categorization Decision Tree\n63: \n64: Before creating a component, answer:\n65: 1. Is it a Shadcn primitive? → `ui/` (lowercase file name)\n66: 2. Is it a modal or dialog overlay? → `modals/` (PascalCase, `Modal` suffix)\n67: 3. Is it small, reusable, and decoupled from any specific page or layout? → `atoms/`\n68: 4. Is it tightly coupled to a specific layout section (nav, sidebar, breadcrumb)? → `shared/`\n69: 5. Is it a page layout wrapper? → `layouts/`\n70: 6. Is it a route access gate? → `guards/`\n71: \n72: ### Inline Component Rule\n73: Never define reusable sub-components as local named functions at the bottom of a page file.\n74: - If it has its own props interface → extract to the correct folder\n75: - If it uses `forwardRef` → extract to `atoms/` or `modals/`\n76: - If it contains its own `useState` or `useEffect` → strong signal to extract\n77: \n78: ---\n79: \n80: ## State Management Patterns\n81: \n82: ### When to Use Each State Type\n83: \n84: | State Type | Use Case | Example |\n85: |------------|----------|---------|\n86: | **Local State** (`useState`) | UI-only state, form inputs, mutation loading | Modal open/close, input values, submitting flag |\n87: | **Redux** (READ thunks) | All server state + global app state | User list, projects, tasks, auth, app settings |\n88: | **Redux** (sync reducers) | Auth state, optimistic updates | loginSuccess, logout, markOneRead |\n89: | **URL State** | Shareable/bookmarkable state | Filters, pagination, search |\n90: \n91: > **Do NOT use TanStack Query.** All data fetching uses Redux async thunks (`createAsyncThunk` in service files). Mutations use direct service calls with local `useState` for loading.\n92: \n93: ### Redux Toolkit Slice Pattern\n94: \n95: ```typescript\n96: // GOOD: Typed slice with initial state\n97: import { createSlice, PayloadAction } from '@reduxjs/toolkit';\n98: import type { AuthState, AuthUser } from '@/types/redux/auth';\n99: \n100: const initialState: AuthState = {\n101:     user: null,\n102:     isAuthenticated: false,\n103:     isLoading: false,\n104:     error: null,\n105: };\n106: \n107: export const authSlice = createSlice({\n108:     name: 'auth',\n109:     initialState,\n110:     reducers: {\n111:         loginStart: (state) => {\n112:             state.isLoading = true;\n113:             state.error = null;\n114:         },\n115:         loginSuccess: (state, action: PayloadAction<AuthUser>) => {\n116:             state.user = action.payload;\n117:             state.isAuthenticated = true;\n118:             state.isLoading = false;\n119:         },\n120:         loginFailure: (state, action: PayloadAction<string>) => {\n121:             state.isLoading = false;\n122:             state.error = action.payload;\n123:         },\n124:         logout: (state) => {\n125:             state.user = null;\n126:             state.isAuthenticated = false;\n127:         },\n128:     },\n129: });\n130: \n131: export const { loginStart, loginSuccess, loginFailure, logout } = authSlice.actions;\n132: ```\n133: \n134: ### React Query Key Factory Pattern\n135: \n136: ```typescript\n137: // GOOD: Centralized query key factory\n138: export const authKeys = {\n139:     all: ['auth'] as const,\n140:     user: () => [...authKeys.all, 'user'] as const,\n141:     session: () => [...authKeys.all, 'session'] as const,\n142: };\n143: \n144: export const userKeys = {\n145:     all: ['users'] as const,\n146:     lists: () => [...userKeys.all, 'list'] as const,\n147:     list: (filters: UserFilters) => [...userKeys.lists(), filters] as const,\n148:     details: () => [...userKeys.all, 'detail'] as const,\n149:     detail: (id: string) => [...userKeys.details(), id] as const,\n150: };\n151: \n152: // Usage in hooks\n153: export function useUser(id: string) {\n154:     return useQuery({\n155:         queryKey: userKeys.detail(id),\n156:         queryFn: () => userService.getById(id),\n157:     });\n158: }\n159: ```\n160: \n161: ### React Query with Mutations\n162: \n163: ```typescript\n164: // GOOD: Mutation with cache invalidation\n165: export function useLogin() {\n166:     const queryClient = useQueryClient();\n167:     const dispatch = useAppDispatch();\n168: \n169:     return useMutation({\n170:         mutationFn: (data: LoginRequest) => authService.login(data),\n171:         onSuccess: (response) => {\n172:             dispatch(loginSuccess(response.data.user));\n173:             queryClient.invalidateQueries({ queryKey: authKeys.all });\n174:         },\n175:         onError: (error) => {\n176:             dispatch(loginFailure(error.message));\n177:         },\n178:     });\n179: }\n180: ```\n181: \n182: ---\n183: \n184: ## Form Handling — MANDATORY: React Hook Form + Zod + shadcn Form\n185: \n186: > **ALL forms MUST use this pattern. Manual `useState` for form fields is FORBIDDEN.**\n187: \n188: ### Zod Schema Definition\n189: \n190: ```typescript\n191: // GOOD: Schema with custom error messages\n192: import { z } from 'zod';\n193: \n194: export const loginSchema = z.object({\n195:     username: z.string().min(1, 'Username is required'),\n196:     password: z.string().min(6, 'Password must be at least 6 characters'),\n197:     rememberMe: z.boolean().optional(),\n198: });\n199: \n200: export type LoginFormData = z.infer<typeof loginSchema>;\n201: \n202: // Schema with cross-field validation\n203: export const registerSchema = z\n204:     .object({\n205:         username: z.string().min(3, 'Username must be at least 3 characters'),\n206:         email: z.string().email('Invalid email address').optional(),\n207:         password: z.string().min(8, 'Password must be at least 8 characters'),\n208:         confirmPassword: z.string(),\n209:     })\n210:     .refine((data) => data.password === data.confirmPassword, {\n211:         message: 'Passwords do not match',\n212:         path: ['confirmPassword'],\n213:     });\n214: ```\n215: \n216: ### Form Component Pattern (MANDATORY)\n217: \n218: ```typescript\n219: // GOOD: Form with React Hook Form + Zod + shadcn Form components\n220: import { useForm } from 'react-hook-form';\n221: import { zodResolver } from '@hookform/resolvers/zod';\n222: import { loginSchema, type LoginFormData } from '~/utils/validations/auth';\n223: import { Form, FormField, FormItem, FormLabel, FormControl, FormMessage } from '~/components/ui/form';\n224: import { Input } from '~/components/ui/input';\n225: import { Button } from '~/components/ui/button';\n226: \n227: export function LoginForm() {\n228:     const form = useForm<LoginFormData>({\n229:         resolver: zodResolver(loginSchema),\n230:         defaultValues: { username: '', password: '' },\n231:     });\n232: \n233:     const onSubmit = (data: LoginFormData) => { /* ... */ };\n234: \n235:     return (\n236:         <Form {...form}>\n237:             <form onSubmit={form.handleSubmit(onSubmit)}>\n238:                 <FormField control={form.control} name=\"username\" render={({ field }) => (\n239:                     <FormItem>\n240:                         <FormLabel>Username</FormLabel>\n241:                         <FormControl><Input placeholder=\"Username\" {...field} /></FormControl>\n242:                         <FormMessage />\n243:                     </FormItem>\n244:                 )} />\n245:                 <FormField control={form.control} name=\"password\" render={({ field }) => (\n246:                     <FormItem>\n247:                         <FormLabel>Password</FormLabel>\n248:                         <FormControl><Input type=\"password\" placeholder=\"Password\" {...field} /></FormControl>\n249:                         <FormMessage />\n250:                     </FormItem>\n251:                 )} />\n252:                 <Button type=\"submit\">Login</Button>\n253:             </form>\n254:         </Form>\n255:     );\n256: }\n257: ```\n258: \n259: ---\n260: \n261: ## Tailwind CSS + Shadcn/UI Patterns\n262: \n263: ### Class Composition with cn()\n264: \n265: ```typescript\n266: // lib/utils.ts\n267: import { clsx, type ClassValue } from 'clsx';\n268: import { twMerge } from 'tailwind-merge';\n269: \n270: export function cn(...inputs: ClassValue[]) {\n271:     return twMerge(clsx(inputs));\n272: }\n273: \n274: // Usage\n275: <div className={cn(\n276:     'flex items-center gap-2',\n277:     isActive && 'bg-blue-100',\n278:     disabled && 'opacity-50 cursor-not-allowed'\n279: )} />\n280: ```\n281: \n282: ### Component Variants with cva\n283: \n284: ```typescript\n285: import { cva, type VariantProps } from 'class-variance-authority';\n286: \n287: const buttonVariants = cva(\n288:     'inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-md font-medium transition-colors',\n289:     {\n290:         variants: {\n291:             variant: {\n292:                 primary: 'bg-primary text-white hover:bg-primary/90',\n293:                 outline: 'border border-input bg-background hover:bg-accent',\n294:                 ghost: 'hover:bg-accent hover:text-accent-foreground',\n295:             },\n296:             size: {\n297:                 sm: 'h-8 px-3 text-sm',\n298:                 md: 'h-10 px-4',\n299:                 lg: 'h-12 px-6 text-lg',\n300:             },\n301:         },\n302:         defaultVariants: {\n303:             variant: 'primary',\n304:             size: 'md',\n305:         },\n306:     }\n307: );\n308: \n309: interface ButtonProps extends VariantProps<typeof buttonVariants> {\n310:     children: React.ReactNode;\n311: }\n312: \n313: export function Button({ variant, size, children }: ButtonProps) {\n314:     return <button className={buttonVariants({ variant, size })}>{children}</button>;\n315: }\n316: ```\n317: \n318: > **Variant-First Rule (MANDATORY):** All reusable components MUST use cva variants for visual differences that appear across call sites. The `className` prop is for call-site-local overrides only (width, height, spacing, positioning). Never copy-paste a group of Tailwind classes across multiple call sites — extract it as a variant. Every reusable component MUST accept a `className` prop.\n319: \n320: ### Responsive Design\n321: \n322: ```typescript\n323: // Mobile-first responsive pattern\n324: <div className=\"\n325:     grid grid-cols-1          /* Mobile: 1 column */\n326:     sm:grid-cols-2            /* Tablet: 2 columns */\n327:     lg:grid-cols-3            /* Desktop: 3 columns */\n328:     gap-4\n329: \">\n330:     {items.map(item => <Card key={item.id} {...item} />)}\n331: </div>\n332: \n333: // Hide/show based on screen size\n334: <nav className=\"hidden md:flex\">Desktop nav</nav>\n335: <nav className=\"flex md:hidden\">Mobile nav</nav>\n336: ```\n337: \n338: ---\n339: \n340: ## Socket.IO Frontend Patterns\n341: \n342: ### Frontend Socket Service Pattern\n343: \n344: ```typescript\n345: // GOOD: Singleton service with typed events\n346: class ChatSocketService {\n347:     private socket: Socket | null = null;\n348: \n349:     connect(): Socket {\n350:         if (this.socket?.connected) return this.socket;\n351: \n352:         this.socket = io('/chat', {\n353:             withCredentials: true,  // Send cookies\n354:             transports: ['websocket', 'polling'],\n355:             reconnection: true,\n356:             reconnectionAttempts: 5,\n357:         });\n358: \n359:         return this.socket;\n360:     }\n361: \n362:     onNewMessage(callback: (event: NewMessageEvent) => void): void {\n363:         this.socket?.on('message:new', callback);\n364:     }\n365: \n366:     offNewMessage(): void {\n367:         this.socket?.off('message:new');\n368:     }\n369: }\n370: \n371: export const chatSocketService = new ChatSocketService();\n372: ```\n373: \n374: ### React Hook Pattern for Socket Rooms\n375: \n376: ```typescript\n377: // GOOD: Hook with proper cleanup and React Query integration\n378: export function useChatRoomSocket({ roomId, enabled = true }) {\n379:     const queryClient = useQueryClient();\n380: \n381:     useEffect(() => {\n382:         if (!enabled || !chatSocketService.isConnected()) return;\n383: \n384:         chatSocketService.joinRoom(roomId);\n385: \n386:         const handleNewMessage = (event: NewMessageEvent) => {\n387:             if (event.roomId !== roomId) return;\n388: \n389:             // Update React Query cache directly for instant UI update\n390:             queryClient.setQueryData<ChatMessage[]>(\n391:                 chatKeys.messages(roomId),\n392:                 (old = []) => [...old, event.message]\n393:             );\n394:         };\n395: \n396:         chatSocketService.onNewMessage(handleNewMessage);\n397: \n398:         return () => {\n399:             chatSocketService.offNewMessage();\n400:             chatSocketService.leaveRoom(roomId);\n401:         };\n402:     }, [roomId, enabled, queryClient]);\n403: }\n404: ```\n405: \n406: ---\n407: \n408: ## Related Guides\n409: \n410: For more detailed patterns, see:\n411: - [Component Patterns](component-patterns.md) - Detailed component structure\n412: - [Data Fetching](data-fetching.md) - API integration patterns\n413: - [TanStack Query](tanstack-query.md) - Query patterns\n414: - [TypeScript Standards](typescript-standards.md) - Type safety guidelines\n415: - [Authentication Architecture](authentication-architecture.md) - Auth flow details\n416: \n417: ---\n418: \n419: ## Playwright E2E Testing\n420: \n421: ### Page Object Model Pattern\n422: \n423: ```typescript\n424: // test/page-objects/login.page.ts\n425: import { Locator, Page } from '@playwright/test';\n426: \n427: export class LoginPage {\n428:     readonly page: Page;\n429:     readonly usernameInput: Locator;\n430:     readonly passwordInput: Locator;\n431:     readonly submitButton: Locator;\n432:     readonly errorMessage: Locator;\n433: \n434:     constructor(page: Page) {\n435:         this.page = page;\n436:         this.usernameInput = page.getByTestId('username-input');\n437:         this.passwordInput = page.getByTestId('password-input');\n438:         this.submitButton = page.getByRole('button', { name: /login/i });\n439:         this.errorMessage = page.getByRole('alert');\n440:     }\n441: \n442:     async goto() {\n443:         await this.page.goto('/auth/login');\n444:     }\n445: \n446:     async login(username: string, password: string) {\n447:         await this.usernameInput.fill(username);\n448:         await this.passwordInput.fill(password);\n449:         await this.submitButton.click();\n450:     }\n451: \n452:     async expectErrorMessage(message: string) {\n453:         await expect(this.errorMessage).toContainText(message);\n454:     }\n455: }\n456: ```\n457: \n458: ### Custom Test Fixtures\n459: \n460: ```typescript\n461: // test/fixtures/auth.fixture.ts\n462: import { test as base } from '@playwright/test';\n463: import { LoginPage } from '../page-objects/login.page';\n464: \n465: type AuthFixtures = {\n466:     loginPage: LoginPage;\n467:     login: (username: string, password: string) => Promise<void>;\n468: };\n469: \n470: export const test = base.extend<AuthFixtures>({\n471:     loginPage: async ({ page }, use) => {\n472:         const loginPage = new LoginPage(page);\n473:         await use(loginPage);\n474:     },\n475:     login: async ({ page }, use) => {\n476:         const loginFn = async (username: string, password: string) => {\n477:             const loginPage = new LoginPage(page);\n478:             await loginPage.goto();\n479:             await loginPage.login(username, password);\n480:             await page.waitForURL('/dashboard');\n481:         };\n482:         await use(loginFn);\n483:     },\n484: });\n485: \n486: export { expect } from '@playwright/test';\n487: ```\n488: \n489: ### Test Structure\n490: \n491: ```typescript\n492: // test/tests/auth/login.spec.ts\n493: import { test, expect } from '../../fixtures/auth.fixture';\n494: \n495: test.describe('Login Page', () => {\n496:     test.beforeEach(async ({ loginPage }) => {\n497:         await loginPage.goto();\n498:     });\n499: \n500:     test('should display login form', async ({ loginPage }) => {\n501:         await expect(loginPage.usernameInput).toBeVisible();\n502:         await expect(loginPage.passwordInput).toBeVisible();\n503:         await expect(loginPage.submitButton).toBeVisible();\n504:     });\n505: \n506:     test('should show error for invalid credentials', async ({ loginPage }) => {\n507:         await loginPage.login('invalid', 'wrong');\n508:         await loginPage.expectErrorMessage('Invalid credentials');\n509:     });\n510: \n511:     test('should redirect to dashboard on success', async ({ page, login }) => {\n512:         await login('admin@example.com', 'Password123!');\n513:         await expect(page).toHaveURL('/dashboard');\n514:     });\n515: });\n516: ```\n517: \n518: ---\n519: \n520: ## MANDATORY Rules (from Base Architecture)\n521: \n522: ### Utility Function Rules\n523: \n524: - **Arrow function syntax only**: `export const fn = (...): ReturnType => { ... }` — NEVER `function` declarations\n525: - **Location**: All utility functions MUST live in `app/utils/` organized by domain:\n526:   - `utils/formatting.ts` — Date/time, number, string formatting\n527:   - `utils/badges.ts` — CSS class mapping for badges, status indicators\n528:   - `utils/avatar.ts` — Avatar color generation, initials extraction\n529:   - `utils/pagination.ts` — Page number calculation, pagination helpers\n530:   - `utils/csv.ts` — CSV export/download utilities\n531:   - `utils/dates.ts` — Date arithmetic, trend calculations\n532: - **Never inline**: Helper functions that are NOT React components or hooks MUST NOT be defined inside page/component files\n533: - **Named exports only**: Use `export const`, never `export default` for utility functions\n534: - **Deduplication**: If utility is needed in multiple files, extract to `utils/` — never copy-paste\n535: \n536: ### Service & Slice Pattern\n537: \n538: - `createAsyncThunk` MUST NOT appear in slice files (`redux/features/*Slice.ts`)\n539: - All thunks live in service files (`services/httpServices/*Service.ts`)\n540: - Slice files only contain: thunk imports, initial state, sync reducers, `extraReducers`\n541: - Consumer pages/components import thunks from service files, not slice files\n542: \n543: ### Type Organization\n544: \n545: - ALL interfaces and types defined in `types/*.d.ts` — NONE inline in components, pages, hooks, or utils\n546: - Component `*Props` interfaces in domain type file or `types/components.d.ts`\n547: - Types imported with `import type` syntax\n548: - No duplicate type names across files\n549: \n550: ### Code Quality Mandates\n551: \n552: - **No `any` type** — use specific types or `unknown` with type guards\n553: - **No `console.log`** in production code — use proper logger\n554: - **No hardcoded mock data** arrays in production components\n555: - **No placeholder data** (John Doe, lorem ipsum, test@example.com)\n556: - **No commented-out code** — delete it, git has history\n557: - **Components < 300 lines** (excluding imports/exports) — split if larger\n558: - **Nesting depth < 5 levels** — extract sub-components if deeper\n559: - **httpService wrapper required** — no raw axios/fetch calls in components or slices\n560: - **No direct API calls** in components or Redux slices — always go through service layer\n561: \n562: ### Import Order\n563: \n564: 1. React / React Router\n565: 2. External libraries (Redux, Zod, etc.)\n566: 3. Internal aliases (`~/components`, `~/services`, etc.)\n567: 4. Relative imports\n568: 5. Type imports (with `import type`)\n569: 6. Styles\n\n(End of file - total 569 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Frontend Best Practices\n\n## React Component Best Practices\n\n### Component File Organization\n\n```typescript\n// GOOD: Component with typed props, hooks at top\ninterface ButtonProps {\n    variant?: 'primary' | 'outline';\n    children: React.ReactNode;\n    onClick?: () => void;\n    disabled?: boolean;\n}\n\nexport function Button({ variant = 'primary', children, onClick, disabled }: ButtonProps) {\n    const { t } = useTranslation();\n    const [isLoading, setIsLoading] = useState(false);\n\n    const handleClick = () => {","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".claude/react/docs/best-practices.md","time":{"start":1779192392381,"end":1779192392667}},"id":"prt_e402165d0001GWPagJbjc1C542","sessionID":"ses_1bfdeff9cffel20XYIHhGhKvJ3","messageID":"msg_e40213fe2001selwtPtEjGbkJE"}}
